{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894923848,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b960524001ON8JJuQQQc95qm","messageID":"msg_d7b95eadb001oBFV4LvjF98OMf","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_266bcde70b924e88a39a7d9a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-043 AgentCube Technical Implementation\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the comprehensive technical implementation details for the AgentCube platform. It covers the system architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling strategies, and testing approaches for all core components.\n6: \n7: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents that provisions isolated sandbox environments on demand, routes HTTP traffic through session-aware proxies, and manages the complete sandbox lifecycle.\n8: \n9: ## Architecture\n10: \n11: ### System Architecture\n12: \n13: ```\n14:                                     ┌─────────────────┐\n15:                                     │   Client/SDK    │\n16:                                     │   (Python/Go)   │\n17:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n18:                                              │\n19:                                     ┌────────▼────────┐\n20:                                     │   Ingress/LB    │\n21:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n22:                                              │\n23:                                     ┌────────▼────────┐\n24:                           ┌─────────│   Router (:8080)│─────────┐\n25:                           │         └────────┬────────┘         │\n26:                           │                  │                  │\n27:                 ┌─────────▼─────────┐ ┌──────▼──────┐ ┌────────▼────────┐\n28:                 │  Workload Manager  │ │Session Store│ │    Agentd       │\n29:                 │   (:8081)          │ │   (Redis)   │ │  (Cleanup)      │\n30:                 └─────────┬─────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n31:                           │\n32:                           │ K8s API\n33:                           ▼\n34:                 ┌─────────────────────┐\n35:                 │   Sandbox Pods      │\n36:                 │  ┌─────┐ ┌─────┐   │\n37:                 │  │Pod 1│ │Pod 2│...│\n38:                 │  └─────┘ └─────┘   │\n39:                 └─────────────────────┘\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Component Architecture\n43: \n44: #### Router Component\n45: \n46: ```\n47: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n48: │                      Router                                  │\n49: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n50: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │\n51: │  │   HTTP       │  │   Session    │  │   Auth       │      │\n52: │  │   Server     │  │   Router     │  │   Middleware │      │\n53: │  │   (Gin)      │  │              │  │   (JWT/K8s)  │      │\n54: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │\n55: │                                                              │\n56: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │\n57: │  │   Rate       │  │   Health     │  │   Proxy      │      │\n58: │  │   Limiter    │  │   Checker    │  │   Handler    │      │\n59: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │\n60: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n61: ```\n62: \n63: #### Workload Manager Component\n64: \n65: ```\n66: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n67: │                   Workload Manager                           │\n68: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n69: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │\n70: │  │   Sandbox    │  │   Resource   │  │   Scheduler  │      │\n71: │  │   Processor  │  │   Manager    │  │              │      │\n72: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │\n73: │                                                              │\n74: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │\n75: │  │   Reconciler │  │   Garbage    │  │   K8s Client │      │\n76: │  │              │  │   Collector  │  │   (client-go)│      │\n77: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │\n78: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n79: ```\n80: \n81: #### Session Store Component\n82: \n83: ```\n84: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n85: │                     Session Store                            │\n86: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n87: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │\n88: │  │   Singleton  │  │   Redis      │  │   Valkey     │      │\n89: │  │   Factory    │  │   Store      │  │   Store      │      │\n90: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │\n91: │                                                              │\n92: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n93: │  │                   Data Structures                     │   │\n94: │  │  session:{id} (JSON) | session:expiry (ZSET)         │   │\n95: │  │  session:last_activity (ZSET)                        │   │\n96: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Integration Points\n101: \n102: | Component | Integration | Protocol | Purpose |\n103: |-----------|-------------|----------|---------|\n104: | Router | Session Store | Redis Protocol | Session state lookup |\n105: | Router | Workload Manager | HTTP/gRPC | Sandbox discovery |\n106: | Workload Manager | Kubernetes API | HTTPS | Resource management |\n107: | Agentd | Session Store | Redis Protocol | Idle detection |\n108: | Agentd | Kubernetes API | HTTPS | Sandbox cleanup |\n109: | SDK/CLI | Router | HTTP/HTTPS | Client operations |\n110: \n111: ## Data Structures\n112: \n113: ### Core Types\n114: \n115: #### SandboxInfo\n116: \n117: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: type SandboxInfo struct {\n121:     // Kind is the type of resource\n122:     Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n123:     \n124:     // SandboxID is the unique identifier for the sandbox\n125:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n126:     \n127:     // SandboxNamespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n128:     SandboxNamespace string `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n129:     \n130:     // Name is the human-readable name\n131:     Name string `json:\"name\"`\n132:     \n133:     // EntryPoints are the access endpoints\n134:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n135:     \n136:     // SessionID is the associated session identifier\n137:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n138:     \n139:     // CreatedAt is the creation timestamp\n140:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n141:     \n142:     // ExpiresAt is the expiration timestamp\n143:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n144:     \n145:     // Status is the current state\n146:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n147:     \n148:     // LastActivity is the last activity timestamp\n149:     LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: #### SandboxEntryPoint\n154: \n155: ```go\n156: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n157:     // Path is the URL path\n158:     Path string `json:\"path\"`\n159:     \n160:     // Protocol is the protocol (http, https, ws, wss)\n161:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n162:     \n163:     // Endpoint is the full endpoint URL\n164:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: #### SessionContext\n169: \n170: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router/session`\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: type SessionContext struct {\n174:     // ID is the unique session identifier\n175:     ID string `json:\"id\"`\n176:     \n177:     // ClientID is the client identifier\n178:     ClientID string `json:\"clientId\"`\n179:     \n180:     // SandboxID is the assigned sandbox\n181:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n182:     \n183:     // CreatedAt is the creation time\n184:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n185:     \n186:     // ExpiresAt is the expiration time\n187:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n188:     \n189:     // LastActivity is the last activity time\n190:     LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n191:     \n192:     // Metadata contains custom key-value pairs\n193:     Metadata map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n194: }\n195: ```\n196: \n197: #### JWTClaims\n198: \n199: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router/auth`\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: type JWTClaims struct {\n203:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n204:     \n205:     // UserID is the user identifier\n206:     UserID string `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n207:     \n208:     // Namespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n209:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n210:     \n211:     // Roles are the assigned roles\n212:     Roles []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n213:     \n214:     // Permissions are the granted permissions\n215:     Permissions []string `json:\"permissions,omitempty\"`\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### Kubernetes Custom Resources\n220: \n221: #### AgentRuntime\n222: \n223: **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n224: \n225: ```go\n226: type AgentRuntime struct {\n227:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n228:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n229:     \n230:     Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n231:     Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n232: }\n233: \n234: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n235:     // Image is the container image\n236:     Image string `json:\"image\"`\n237:     \n238:     // Resources defines resource requirements\n239:     Resources v1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n240:     \n241:     // Environment variables\n242:     Env []v1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n243:     \n244:     // Ports to expose\n245:     Ports []v1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n246: }\n247: \n248: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n249:     // Phase is the current phase\n250:     Phase AgentRuntimePhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n251:     \n252:     // Conditions represent the latest available observations\n253:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n254:     \n255:     // Endpoints are the access endpoints\n256:     Endpoints []string `json:\"endpoints,omitempty\"`\n257: }\n258: \n259: type AgentRuntimePhase string\n260: \n261: const (\n262:     AgentRuntimePhasePending    AgentRuntimePhase = \"Pending\"\n263:     AgentRuntimePhaseProvisioning AgentRuntimePhase = \"Provisioning\"\n264:     AgentRuntimePhaseRunning    AgentRuntimePhase = \"Running\"\n265:     AgentRuntimePhaseFailed     AgentRuntimePhase = \"Failed\"\n266:     AgentRuntimePhaseTerminating AgentRuntimePhase = \"Terminating\"\n267: )\n268: ```\n269: \n270: #### CodeInterpreter\n271: \n272: **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n273: \n274: ```go\n275: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n276:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n277:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n278:     \n279:     Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n280:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n281: }\n282: \n283: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n284:     // Runtime is the runtime reference\n285:     Runtime string `json:\"runtime\"`\n286:     \n287:     // SessionID is the associated session\n288:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n289:     \n290:     // Resources defines resource requirements\n291:     Resources v1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n292:     \n293:     // Timeout is the execution timeout\n294:     Timeout metav1.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n295: }\n296: \n297: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n298:     // Phase is the current phase\n299:     Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n300:     \n301:     // Conditions represent the latest available observations\n302:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n303:     \n304:     // PodName is the backing pod name\n305:     PodName string `json:\"podName,omitempty\"`\n306:     \n307:     // PodIP is the pod IP address\n308:     PodIP string `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n309:     \n310:     // Endpoints are the access endpoints\n311:     Endpoints []CodeInterpreterEndpoint `json:\"endpoints,omitempty\"`\n312: }\n313: \n314: type CodeInterpreterEndpoint struct {\n315:     Name     string `json:\"name\"`\n316:     Port     int32  `json:\"port\"`\n317:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n318:     URL      string `json:\"url\"`\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Configuration Structures\n323: \n324: #### RouterConfig\n325: \n326: ```go\n327: type RouterConfig struct {\n328:     // Port is the HTTP server port\n329:     Port int `json:\"port\" yaml:\"port\"`\n330:     \n331:     // SessionTimeout is the session TTL\n332:     SessionTimeout time.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout\" yaml:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n333:     \n334:     // MaxSessionsPerClient is the session limit per client\n335:     MaxSessionsPerClient int `json:\"maxSessionsPerClient\" yaml:\"maxSessionsPerClient\"`\n336:     \n337:     // RateLimit configuration\n338:     RateLimit RateLimitConfig `json:\"rateLimit\" yaml:\"rateLimit\"`\n339:     \n340:     // Auth configuration\n341:     Auth AuthConfig `json:\"auth\" yaml:\"auth\"`\n342:     \n343:     // SessionStore configuration\n344:     SessionStore SessionStoreConfig `json:\"sessionStore\" yaml:\"sessionStore\"`\n345: }\n346: \n347: type RateLimitConfig struct {\n348:     // Enabled enables rate limiting\n349:     Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n350:     \n351:     // RequestsPerSecond is the rate limit\n352:     RequestsPerSecond int `json:\"requestsPerSecond\" yaml:\"requestsPerSecond\"`\n353:     \n354:     // BurstSize is the burst capacity\n355:     BurstSize int `json:\"burstSize\" yaml:\"burstSize\"`\n356: }\n357: \n358: type AuthConfig struct {\n359:     // JWT configuration\n360:     JWT JWTConfig `json:\"jwt\" yaml:\"jwt\"`\n361:     \n362:     // K8sTokenAuth enables Kubernetes token authentication\n363:     K8sTokenAuth bool `json:\"k8sTokenAuth\" yaml:\"k8sTokenAuth\"`\n364: }\n365: \n366: type JWTConfig struct {\n367:     // SigningKey is the secret key (HMAC)\n368:     SigningKey string `json:\"signingKey\" yaml:\"signingKey\"`\n369:     \n370:     // SigningMethod is the algorithm (default: HS256)\n371:     SigningMethod string `json:\"signingMethod\" yaml:\"signingMethod\"`\n372:     \n373:     // ExpiryMax is the maximum token expiry\n374:     ExpiryMax time.Duration `json:\"expiryMax\" yaml:\"expiryMax\"`\n375:     \n376:     // SkipPaths are paths that bypass auth\n377:     SkipPaths []string `json:\"skipPaths\" yaml:\"skipPaths\"`\n378: }\n379: \n380: type SessionStoreConfig struct {\n381:     // Type is the store type (redis, valkey)\n382:     Type string `json:\"type\" yaml:\"type\"`\n383:     \n384:     // Redis configuration\n385:     Redis RedisConfig `json:\"redis\" yaml:\"redis\"`\n386:     \n387:     // Valkey configuration\n388:     Valkey ValkeyConfig `json:\"valkey\" yaml:\"valkey\"`\n389: }\n390: \n391: type RedisConfig struct {\n392:     // Addr is the Redis address\n393:     Addr string `json:\"addr\" yaml:\"addr\"`\n394:     \n395:     // Password is the Redis password\n396:     Password string `json:\"password\" yaml:\"password\"`\n397:     \n398:     // DB is the database number\n399:     DB int `json:\"db\" yaml:\"db\"`\n400: }\n401: \n402: type ValkeyConfig struct {\n403:     // Addr is the Valkey address (comma-separated for cluster)\n404:     Addr string `json:\"addr\" yaml:\"addr\"`\n405:     \n406:     // Password is the Valkey password\n407:     Password string `json:\"password\" yaml:\"password\"`\n408:     \n409:     // DisableCache disables client-side caching\n410:     DisableCache bool `json:\"disableCache\" yaml:\"disableCache\"`\n411: }\n412: ```\n413: \n414: #### WorkloadManagerConfig\n415: \n416: ```go\n417: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n418:     // Port is the HTTP server port\n419:     Port int `json:\"port\" yaml:\"port\"`\n420:     \n421:     // DefaultNamespace is the default K8s namespace\n422:     DefaultNamespace string `json:\"defaultNamespace\" yaml:\"defaultNamespace\"`\n423:     \n424:     // ResourceTimeout is the operation timeout\n425:     ResourceTimeout time.Duration `json:\"resourceTimeout\" yaml:\"resourceTimeout\"`\n426:     \n427:     // DefaultResources are the default resource requests\n428:     DefaultResources ResourceConfig `json:\"defaultResources\" yaml:\"defaultResources\"`\n429:     \n430:     // AllowedRuntimes are the permitted runtime types\n431:     AllowedRuntimes []string `json:\"allowedRuntimes\" yaml:\"allowedRuntimes\"`\n432:     \n433:     // GarbageCollector configuration\n434:     GarbageCollector GCConfig `json:\"garbageCollector\" yaml:\"garbageCollector\"`\n435: }\n436: \n437: type ResourceConfig struct {\n438:     // CPURequest is the default CPU request\n439:     CPURequest string `json:\"cpuRequest\" yaml:\"cpuRequest\"`\n440:     \n441:     // MemoryRequest is the default memory request\n442:     MemoryRequest string `json:\"memoryRequest\" yaml:\"memoryRequest\"`\n443:     \n444:     // CPULimit is the default CPU limit\n445:     CPULimit string `json:\"cpuLimit\" yaml:\"cpuLimit\"`\n446:     \n447:     // MemoryLimit is the default memory limit\n448:     MemoryLimit string `json:\"memoryLimit\" yaml:\"memoryLimit\"`\n449: }\n450: \n451: type GCConfig struct {\n452:     // Enabled enables garbage collection\n453:     Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n454:     \n455:     // Interval is the cleanup interval\n456:     Interval time.Duration `json:\"interval\" yaml:\"interval\"`\n457:     \n458:     // IdleTimeout is the idle threshold\n459:     IdleTimeout time.Duration `json:\"idleTimeout\" yaml:\"idleTimeout\"`\n460:     \n461:     // GracePeriod is the termination grace period\n462:     GracePeriod time.Duration `json:\"gracePeriod\" yaml:\"gracePeriod\"`\n463: }\n464: ```\n465: \n466: ## API Contracts\n467: \n468: ### Router API\n469: \n470: #### Session Management\n471: \n472: **Create Session**\n473: \n474: ```http\n475: POST /api/v1/sessions\n476: Content-Type: application/json\n477: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n478: \n479: {\n480:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n481:   \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n482:   \"resources\": {\n483:     \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n484:     \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n485:   },\n486:   \"metadata\": {\n487:     \"user\": \"alice\",\n488:     \"project\": \"demo\"\n489:   }\n490: }\n491: ```\n492: \n493: **Response:**\n494: \n495: ```http\n496: HTTP/1.1 201 Created\n497: Content-Type: application/json\n498: \n499: {\n500:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n501:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc-456\",\n502:   \"status\": \"provisioning\",\n503:   \"endpoints\": [],\n504:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n505:   \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-11T16:30:00Z\"\n506: }\n507: ```\n508: \n509: **Get Session**\n510: \n511: ```http\n512: GET /api/v1/sessions/{sessionId}\n513: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n514: ```\n515: \n516: **Response:**\n517: \n518: ```http\n519: HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n520: Content-Type: application/json\n521: \n522: {\n523:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n524:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc-456\",\n525:   \"status\": \"running\",\n526:   \"endpoints\": [\n527:     {\n528:       \"name\": \"http\",\n529:       \"url\": \"http://sandbox-abc-456.default.svc:8080\"\n530:     }\n531:   ],\n532:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n533:   \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-11T16:30:00Z\",\n534:   \"lastActivity\": \"2026-04-11T15:35:00Z\"\n535: }\n536: ```\n537: \n538: **Delete Session**\n539: \n540: ```http\n541: DELETE /api/v1/sessions/{sessionId}\n542: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n543: ```\n544: \n545: **Response:**\n546: \n547: ```http\n548: HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n549: ```\n550: \n551: #### Proxy Operations\n552: \n553: **Proxy Request**\n554: \n555: ```http\n556: POST /api/v1/proxy/{sandboxId}/*\n557: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n558: X-Session-ID: session-123\n559: ```\n560: \n561: **Behavior:**\n562: 1. Extract session ID from header or path\n563: 2. Validate session exists and is active\n564: 3. Lookup sandbox endpoint from session store\n565: 4. Forward request to sandbox\n566: 5. Return sandbox response\n567: \n568: ### Workload Manager API\n569: \n570: #### Sandbox Operations\n571: \n572: **Create Sandbox**\n573: \n574: ```http\n575: POST /api/v1/sandboxes\n576: Content-Type: application/json\n577: \n578: {\n579:   \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n580:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n581:   \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n582:   \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n583:   \"resources\": {\n584:     \"requests\": {\n585:       \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n586:       \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n587:     },\n588:     \"limits\": {\n589:       \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n590:       \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n591:     }\n592:   }\n593: }\n594: ```\n595: \n596: **Response:**\n597: \n598: ```http\n599: HTTP/1.1 201 Created\n600: Content-Type: application/json\n601: \n602: {\n603:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n604:   \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n605:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n606:   \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n607:   \"podName\": \"\",\n608:   \"endpoints\": [],\n609:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n610: }\n611: ```\n612: \n613: **Get Sandbox**\n614: \n615: ```http\n616: GET /api/v1/sandboxes/{sandboxId}\n617: ```\n618: \n619: **List Sandboxes**\n620: \n621: ```http\n622: GET /api/v1/sandboxes?namespace=default&phase=Running\n623: ```\n624: \n625: **Delete Sandbox**\n626: \n627: ```http\n628: DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{sandboxId}\n629: ```\n630: \n631: ### Store Interface\n632: \n633: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n634: \n635: ```go\n636: type Store interface {\n637:     // Ping checks store connectivity\n638:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n639:     \n640:     // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox by session ID\n641:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n642:     \n643:     // StoreSandbox persists new sandbox\n644:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n645:     \n646:     // UpdateSandbox updates existing sandbox\n647:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n648:     \n649:     // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n650:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n651:     \n652:     // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes expired before time\n653:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n654:     \n655:     // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes inactive before time\n656:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n657:     \n658:     // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates last activity time\n659:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n660:     \n661:     // Close closes the store connection\n662:     Close() error\n663: }\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ## Error Handling\n667: \n668: ### Error Types\n669: \n670: #### Router Errors\n671: \n672: ```go\n673: package router\n674: \n675: var (\n676:     // Session errors\n677:     ErrSessionNotFound     = errors.New(\"router: session not found\")\n678:     ErrSessionExpired      = errors.New(\"router: session expired\")\n679:     ErrSessionLimitReached = errors.New(\"router: session limit reached\")\n680:     \n681:     // Sandbox errors\n682:     ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"router: sandbox not found\")\n683:     ErrSandboxNotReady     = errors.New(\"router: sandbox not ready\")\n684:     \n685:     // Auth errors\n686:     ErrUnauthorized        = errors.New(\"router: unauthorized\")\n687:     ErrForbidden           = errors.New(\"router: forbidden\")\n688:     ErrInvalidToken        = errors.New(\"router: invalid token\")\n689:     \n690:     // Rate limit errors\n691:     ErrRateLimitExceeded   = errors.New(\"router: rate limit exceeded\")\n692: )\n693: ```\n694: \n695: #### Workload Manager Errors\n696: \n697: ```go\n698: package workloadmanager\n699: \n700: var (\n701:     // Sandbox errors\n702:     ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: sandbox not found\")\n703:     ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: sandbox already exists\")\n704:     ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: invalid runtime type\")\n705:     ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: sandbox validation failed\")\n706:     ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: sandbox creation timeout\")\n707:     \n708:     // Resource errors\n709:     ErrResourceQuotaExceeded = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: resource quota exceeded\")\n710:     ErrInsufficientResources = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: insufficient cluster resources\")\n711:     \n712:     // K8s API errors\n713:     ErrK8sAPIFailure       = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: Kubernetes API error\")\n714:     ErrResourceVersionConflict = errors.New(\"workloadmanager: resource version conflict\")\n715: )\n716: ```\n717: \n718: #### Store Errors\n719: \n720: ```go\n721: package store\n722: \n723: var (\n724:     ErrNotFound        = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n725:     ErrConnectionFailed = errors.New(\"store: connection failed\")\n726:     ErrSerialization   = errors.New(\"store: serialization error\")\n727:     ErrTransactionFailed = errors.New(\"store: transaction failed\")\n728: )\n729: ```\n730: \n731: ### Error Response Format\n732: \n733: **Standard Error Response:**\n734: \n735: ```json\n736: {\n737:   \"error\": {\n738:     \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\",\n739:     \"message\": \"Session 'session-123' not found\",\n740:     \"details\": {\n741:       \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n742:       \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n743:     }\n744:   }\n745: }\n746: ```\n747: \n748: **HTTP Status Code Mapping:**\n749: \n750: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code |\n751: |------------|-------------|------------|\n752: | NotFound | 404 | `{RESOURCE}_NOT_FOUND` |\n753: | AlreadyExists | 409 | `{RESOURCE}_ALREADY_EXISTS` |\n754: | Unauthorized | 401 | `UNAUTHORIZED` |\n755: | Forbidden | 403 | `FORBIDDEN` |\n756: | InvalidInput | 400 | `INVALID_INPUT` |\n757: | ValidationFailed | 422 | `VALIDATION_FAILED` |\n758: | RateLimitExceeded | 429 | `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED` |\n759: | InternalError | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` |\n760: | ServiceUnavailable | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` |\n761: | Timeout | 504 | `TIMEOUT` |\n762: \n763: ### Retry Strategy\n764: \n765: **Transient Error Handling:**\n766: \n767: ```go\n768: type RetryConfig struct {\n769:     // MaxRetries is the maximum number of retries\n770:     MaxRetries int\n771:     \n772:     // InitialDelay is the initial backoff duration\n773:     InitialDelay time.Duration\n774:     \n775:     // MaxDelay is the maximum backoff duration\n776:     MaxDelay time.Duration\n777:     \n778:     // Multiplier is the backoff multiplier\n779:     Multiplier float64\n780: }\n781: \n782: var DefaultRetryConfig = RetryConfig{\n783:     MaxRetries:   3,\n784:     InitialDelay: 100 * time.Millisecond,\n785:     MaxDelay:     2 * time.Second,\n786:     Multiplier:   2.0,\n787: }\n788: ```\n789: \n790: **Retryable Errors:**\n791: - `TooManyRequests` (429) - Respect `Retry-After` header\n792: - `ServiceUnavailable` (503) - Exponential backoff\n793: - `Timeout` (504) - Exponential backoff\n794: - `ConnectionRefused` - Exponential backoff\n795: \n796: **Non-Retryable Errors:**\n797: - `NotFound` (404)\n798: - `BadRequest` (400)\n799: - `Unauthorized` (401)\n800: - `Forbidden` (403)\n801: - `Conflict` (409)\n802: \n803: ### Error Wrapping\n804: \n805: ```go\n806: // Example: Error wrapping with context\n807: func (p *SandboxProcessor) Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n808:     if err := p.validate(sandbox); err != nil {\n809:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"validate sandbox: %w\", ErrValidationFailed)\n810:     }\n811:     \n812:     created, err := p.client.CodeInterpreters(sandbox.Namespace).Create(ctx, obj, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n813:     if err != nil {\n814:         if errors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n815:             return nil, ErrSandboxExists\n816:         }\n817:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create CodeInterpreter: %w\", err)\n818:     }\n819:     \n820:     return created, nil\n821: }\n822: ```\n823: \n824: ## Testing Strategy\n825: \n826: ### Test Pyramid\n827: \n828: ```\n829:                     /\\\n830:                    /  \\\n831:                   / E2E \\\n832:                  /-------\\\n833:                 /         \\\n834:                /Integration\\\n835:               /-------------\\\n836:              /               \\\n837:             /    Unit Tests   \\\n838:            /-------------------\\\n839: ```\n840: \n841: ### Unit Tests\n842: \n843: #### Router Unit Tests\n844: \n845: **File:** `pkg/router/router_test.go`\n846: \n847: ```go\n848: // Test cases\n849: - TestRouter_HealthCheck\n850: - TestRouter_ReadyCheck\n851: - TestRouter_CreateSession_Success\n852: - TestRouter_CreateSession_InvalidInput\n853: - TestRouter_CreateSession_SessionLimit\n854: - TestRouter_GetSession_Success\n855: - TestRouter_GetSession_NotFound\n856: - TestRouter_DeleteSession_Success\n857: - TestRouter_ProxyRequest_Success\n858: - TestRouter_ProxyRequest_SessionExpired\n859: - TestRouter_ProxyRequest_SandboxNotReady\n860: ```\n861: \n862: **Example:**\n863: \n864: ```go\n865: func TestRouter_CreateSession_Success(t *testing.T) {\n866:     // Setup\n867:     config := &RouterConfig{\n868:         SessionTimeout: 1 * time.Hour,\n869:         MaxSessionsPerClient: 10,\n870:     }\n871:     router := NewTestRouter(config)\n872:     \n873:     // Execute\n874:     req := &CreateSessionRequest{\n875:         SessionID: \"test-session\",\n876:         Runtime:   \"python-3.11\",\n877:     }\n878:     resp, err := router.CreateSession(context.Background(), req)\n879:     \n880:     // Assert\n881:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n882:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-session\", resp.SessionID)\n883:     assert.Equal(t, \"provisioning\", resp.Status)\n884: }\n885: ```\n886: \n887: #### Workload Manager Unit Tests\n888: \n889: **File:** `pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n890: \n891: ```go\n892: // Test cases\n893: - TestCreateSandbox_Success\n894: - TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime\n895: - TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists\n896: - TestUpdateSandbox_Success\n897: - TestDeleteSandbox_Success\n898: - TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound\n899: - TestGetSandbox_Success\n900: - TestValidateSandbox_NilContext\n901: - TestValidateSandbox_MissingNamespace\n902: ```\n903: \n904: **Example:**\n905: \n906: ```go\n907: func TestCreateSandbox_Success(t *testing.T) {\n908:     // Setup\n909:     client := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n910:     processor := newTestProcessor(client)\n911:     ctx := newTestSandboxContext(\"test-sandbox\", \"python\")\n912:     \n913:     // Execute\n914:     sandbox, err := processor.Create(context.Background(), ctx)\n915:     \n916:     // Assert\n917:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n918:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-sandbox\", sandbox.Name)\n919:     assert.Equal(t, \"Pending\", string(sandbox.Status.Phase))\n920: }\n921: ```\n922: \n923: #### Store Unit Tests\n924: \n925: **File:** `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`, `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n926: \n927: ```go\n928: // Test cases\n929: - TestPing_Success\n930: - TestGetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound\n931: - TestStoreSandbox_NilRejected\n932: - TestStoreSandbox_ZeroExpiresAtRejected\n933: - TestStoreSandbox_Atomicity\n934: - TestUpdateSandbox_MissingKey\n935: - TestDeleteSandboxBySessionID_FullCleanup\n936: - TestListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanTolerance\n937: - TestUpdateSessionLastActivity_MissingSession\n938: - TestStorage_Singleton\n939: ```\n940: \n941: ### Integration Tests\n942: \n943: #### Router Integration Tests\n944: \n945: **File:** `test/integration/router/session_test.go`\n946: \n947: ```go\n948: // Test cases\n949: - TestSession_Lifecycle\n950: - TestSession_ProxyToSandbox\n951: - TestSession_Authentication_JWT\n952: - TestSession_Authentication_K8sToken\n953: - TestSession_RateLimiting\n954: - TestSession_ConcurrentAccess\n955: ```\n956: \n957: **Example:**\n958: \n959: ```go\n960: func TestSession_Lifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n961:     // Setup\n962:     routerURL := getRouterURL()\n963:     token := generateTestToken()\n964:     \n965:     // Create session\n966:     session := createSession(t, routerURL, token)\n967:     \n968:     // Wait for sandbox to be ready\n969:     waitForSandboxReady(t, routerURL, session.ID, token)\n970:     \n971:     // Proxy request\n972:     response := proxyRequest(t, routerURL, session.ID, token)\n973:     assert.Equal(t, 200, response.StatusCode)\n974:     \n975:     // Delete session\n976:     deleteSession(t, routerURL, session.ID, token)\n977:     \n978:     // Verify deletion\n979:     session = getSession(t, routerURL, session.ID, token)\n980:     assert.Equal(t, 404, session.StatusCode)\n981: }\n982: ```\n983: \n984: #### Workload Manager Integration Tests\n985: \n986: **File:** `test/integration/workloadmanager/sandbox_test.go`\n987: \n988: ```go\n989: // Test cases\n990: - TestSandbox_FullLifecycle\n991: - TestSandbox_ResourceQuotaEnforcement\n992: - TestSandbox_ConcurrentCreation\n993: - TestSandbox_HealthMonitoring\n994: - TestGarbageCollector_IdleCleanup\n995: - TestGarbageCollector_ExpiredCleanup\n996: ```\n997: \n998: #### Store Integration Tests\n999: \n1000: **File:** `pkg/store/integration_test.go`\n1001: \n1002: ```go\n1003: // Test cases (both Redis and Valkey)\n1004: - TestIntegration_StoreAndGet\n1005: - TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex\n1006: - TestIntegration_LastActivityIndex\n1007: - TestIntegration_GC_ListExpired\n1008: - TestIntegration_GC_ListInactive\n1009: - TestIntegration_ConcurrentAccess\n1010: ```\n1011: \n1012: ### End-to-End Tests\n1013: \n1014: **File:** `test/e2e/test_codeinterpreter.py`\n1015: \n1016: ```python\n1017: # Test cases\n1018: - test_codeinterpreter_basic_execution\n1019: - test_codeinterpreter_session_management\n1020: - test_codeinterpreter_resource_limits\n1021: - test_codeinterpreter_cleanup\n1022: ```\n1023: \n1024: **Example:**\n1025: \n1026: ```python\n1027: def test_codeinterpreter_basic_execution():\n1028:     \"\"\"Test basic code execution in sandbox.\"\"\"\n1029:     # Create session\n1030:     session = client.create_session(runtime=\"python-3.11\")\n1031:     \n1032:     # Execute code\n1033:     result = client.execute_code(\n1034:         session_id=session.id,\n1035:         code=\"print('Hello, World!')\"\n1036:     )\n1037:     \n1038:     assert result.status == \"success\"\n1039:     assert \"Hello, World!\" in result.output\n1040:     \n1041:     # Cleanup\n1042:     client.delete_session(session.id)\n1043: ```\n1044: \n1045: ### Test Fixtures\n1046: \n1047: #### Router Test Helpers\n1048: \n1049: ```go\n1050: // pkg/router/test_helpers.go\n1051: \n1052: func newTestRouterConfig() *RouterConfig {\n1053:     return &RouterConfig{\n1054:         Port:               8080,\n1055:         SessionTimeout:     1 * time.Hour,\n1056:         MaxSessionsPerClient: 10,\n1057:         RateLimit: RateLimitConfig{\n1058:             Enabled:           false,\n1059:             RequestsPerSecond: 100,\n1060:         },\n1061:         Auth: AuthConfig{\n1062:             JWT: JWTConfig{\n1063:                 SigningKey:    \"test-secret-key\",\n1064:                 SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n1065:                 ExpiryMax:     24 * time.Hour,\n1066:             },\n1067:         },\n1068:     }\n1069: }\n1070: \n1071: func generateTestToken(claims *JWTClaims) (string, error) {\n1072:     key := []byte(\"test-secret-key\")\n1073:     token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodHS256, claims)\n1074:     return token.SignedString(key)\n1075: }\n1076: \n1077: func newTestClaims(userID, namespace string) *JWTClaims {\n1078:     return &JWTClaims{\n1079:         RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n1080:             ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n1081:             IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n1082:             Subject:   userID,\n1083:         },\n1084:         UserID:    userID,\n1085:         Namespace: namespace,\n1086:         Roles:     []string{\"user\"},\n1087:     }\n1088: }\n1089: ```\n1090: \n1091: #### Workload Manager Test Helpers\n1092: \n1093: ```go\n1094: // pkg/workloadmanager/processor/test_helpers.go\n1095: \n1096: func newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n1097:     return &SandboxContext{\n1098:         Name:        name,\n1099:         Namespace:   \"default\",\n1100:         RuntimeType: runtime,\n1101:         Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n1102:             Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n1103:                 v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n1104:                 v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n1105:             },\n1106:             Limits: v1.ResourceList{\n1107:                 v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"500m\"),\n1108:                 v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"512Mi\"),\n1109:             },\n1110:         },\n1111:     }\n1112: }\n1113: \n1114: func newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n1115:     return &SandboxProcessor{\n1116:         client: client,\n1117:         config: &SandboxConfig{\n1118:             DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n1119:             ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n1120:             AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n1121:         },\n1122:     }\n1123: }\n1124: ```\n1125: \n1126: #### Store Test Helpers\n1127: \n1128: ```go\n1129: // pkg/store/test_helpers.go\n1130: \n1131: func newTestSandbox(sessionID string, expiresAt time.Time) *types.SandboxInfo {\n1132:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n1133:         Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n1134:         SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n1135:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n1136:         Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n1137:         SessionID:        sessionID,\n1138:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n1139:         ExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n1140:         Status:           \"running\",\n1141:         EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n1142:     }\n1143: }\n1144: \n1145: func setupTestRedis(t *testing.T) (*redis.Client, func()) {\n1146:     client := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n1147:         Addr: \"localhost:6379\",\n1148:     })\n1149:     \n1150:     // Flush database\n1151:     client.FlushDB(context.Background())\n1152:     \n1153:     return client, func() {\n1154:         client.Close()\n1155:     }\n1156: }\n1157: ```\n1158: \n1159: ### Test Coverage Targets\n1160: \n1161: | Component | Coverage Target | Priority |\n1162: |-----------|-----------------|----------|\n1163: | Router | 85% | High |\n1164: | Workload Manager | 85% | High |\n1165: | Session Store | 90% | High |\n1166: | Agentd | 80% | Medium |\n1167: | SDK (Python) | 80% | Medium |\n1168: | CLI | 70% | Medium |\n1169: | Integration Tests | N/A | High |\n1170: | E2E Tests | N/A | High |\n1171: \n1172: ### Test Execution\n1173: \n1174: ```bash\n1175: # Run all unit tests\n1176: make test\n1177: \n1178: # Run with coverage\n1179: make test-coverage\n1180: \n1181: # Run integration tests (requires kind cluster)\n1182: make test-integration\n1183: \n1184: # Run E2E tests (requires running cluster)\n1185: make test-e2e\n1186: \n1187: # Run specific package tests\n1188: go test ./pkg/router/...\n1189: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n1190: go test ./pkg/store/...\n1191: \n1192: # Run Python SDK tests\n1193: cd sdk-python && pytest tests/\n1194: \n1195: # Run CLI tests\n1196: cd cmd/cli && pytest tests/\n1197: ```\n1198: \n1199: ## Security Considerations\n1200: \n1201: ### Authentication\n1202: \n1203: 1. **JWT Authentication**: HMAC-SHA256 signed tokens with configurable expiry\n1204: 2. **Kubernetes TokenReview**: Service account token validation via K8s API\n1205: 3. **Token Refresh**: Short-lived access tokens with refresh token rotation\n1206: \n1207: ### Authorization\n1208: \n1209: 1. **RBAC**: Kubernetes Role-Based Access Control for resource operations\n1210: 2. **Namespace Isolation**: Sandboxes restricted to assigned namespaces\n1211: 3. **Resource Quotas**: Per-session and per-client resource limits\n1212: \n1213: ### Network Security\n1214: \n1215: 1. **Network Policies**: Kubernetes NetworkPolicy for pod isolation\n1216: 2. **TLS**: All external communications encrypted with TLS 1.3\n1217: 3. **Service Mesh**: Optional Istio integration for mTLS\n1218: \n1219: ### Data Protection\n1220: \n1221: 1. **Secrets Management**: Kubernetes Secrets for sensitive configuration\n1222: 2. **Encryption at Rest**: Redis/Valkey encryption for session data\n1223: 3. **Audit Logging**: Comprehensive audit trail for all operations\n1224: \n1225: ## Deployment Configuration\n1226: \n1227: ### Environment Variables\n1228: \n1229: #### Router\n1230: \n1231: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n1232: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n1233: | `ROUTER_PORT` | No | `8080` | HTTP server port |\n1234: | `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | No | `3600s` | Session TTL |\n1235: | `MAX_SESSIONS_PER_CLIENT` | No | `10` | Session limit per client |\n1236: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Store backend (redis/valkey) |\n1237: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Redis address |\n1238: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Valkey address |\n1239: | `JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | JWT secret key |\n1240: \n1241: \\* Required based on `STORE_TYPE`\n1242: \n1243: #### Workload Manager\n1244: \n1245: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n1246: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n1247: | `WORKLOAD_PORT` | No | `8081` | HTTP server port |\n1248: | `DEFAULT_NAMESPACE` | No | `default` | Default K8s namespace |\n1249: | `RESOURCE_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Operation timeout |\n1250: | `GC_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable garbage collection |\n1251: | `GC_INTERVAL` | No | `60s` | Cleanup interval |\n1252: | `GC_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `300s` | Idle threshold |\n1253: \n1254: ## File Structure\n1255: \n1256: ```\n1257: agentcube/\n1258: ├── pkg/\n1259: │   ├── router/\n1260: │   │   ├── router.go              # Main router implementation\n1261: │   │   ├── handlers/\n1262: │   │   │   ├── session.go         # Session handlers\n1263: │   │   │   ├── proxy.go           # Proxy handlers\n1264: │   │   │   └── health.go          # Health endpoints\n1265: │   │   ├── middleware/\n1266: │   │   │   ├── auth.go            # Authentication middleware\n1267: │   │   │   ├── ratelimit.go       # Rate limiting\n1268: │   │   │   └── logging.go         # Request logging\n1269: │   │   ├── auth/\n1270: │   │   │   ├── jwt.go             # JWT validation\n1271: │   │   │   ├── k8s.go             # K8s token validation\n1272: │   │   │   └── config.go          # Auth configuration\n1273: │   │   ├── session/\n1274: │   │   │   ├── manager.go         # Session manager\n1275: │   │   │   ├── store.go           # Session store interface\n1276: │   │   │   └── memory_store.go    # In-memory store\n1277: │   │   └── config.go              # Router configuration\n1278: │   │\n1279: │   ├── workloadmanager/\n1280: │   │   ├── server.go              # HTTP server\n1281: │   │   ├── processor/\n1282: │   │   │   ├── sandbox_processor.go  # Sandbox operations\n1283: │   │   │   └── interface.go          # Processor interface\n1284: │   │   ├── reconciler/\n1285: │   │   │   └── reconciler.go      # K8s resource reconciler\n1286: │   │   ├── garbage_collector.go   # Cleanup controller\n1287: │   │   ├── types/\n1288: │   │   │   └── sandbox.go         # Sandbox types\n1289: │   │   └── config.go              # Configuration\n1290: │   │\n1291: │   ├── store/\n1292: │   │   ├── store.go               # Store interface\n1293: │   │   ├── singleton.go           # Singleton factory\n1294: │   │   ├── store_redis.go         # Redis implementation\n1295: │   │   ├── store_valkey.go        # Valkey implementation\n1296: │   │   └── errors.go              # Store errors\n1297: │   │\n1298: │   ├── agentd/\n1299: │   │   ├── agentd.go              # Main daemon\n1300: │   │   ├── cleanup.go             # Cleanup logic\n1301: │   │   └── health.go              # Health checks\n1302: │   │\n1303: │   ├── common/\n1304: │   │   └── types/\n1305: │   │       └── sandbox.go         # Common types\n1306: │   │\n1307: │   └── picod/\n1308: │       ├── server.go              # Picod HTTP server\n1309: │       └── jwt/\n1310: │           ├── middleware.go      # JWT middleware\n1311: │           └── validator.go       # Token validation\n1312: │\n1313: ├── sdk-python/\n1314: │   └── agentcube/\n1315: │       ├── __init__.py\n1316: │       ├── agent_runtime.py       # Agent runtime client\n1317: │       ├── code_interpreter.py    # Code interpreter client\n1318: │       ├── clients/\n1319: │       │   ├── control_plane.py   # Control plane client\n1320: │       │   └── data_plane.py      # Data plane client\n1321: │       ├── utils/\n1322: │       │   ├── http.py            # HTTP utilities\n1323: │       │   └── log.py             # Logging utilities\n1324: │       └── exceptions.py          # SDK exceptions\n1325: │\n1326: ├── cmd/\n1327: │   ├── router/\n1328: │   │   └── main.go                # Router entrypoint\n1329: │   ├── workloadmanager/\n1330: │   │   └── main.go                # Workload manager entrypoint\n1331: │   ├── agentd/\n1332: │   │   └── main.go                # Agentd entrypoint\n1333: │   └── cli/\n1334: │       └── agentcube/\n1335: │           ├── cli/\n1336: │           │   └── main.py        # CLI entrypoint\n1337: │           ├── runtime/\n1338: │           │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n1339: │           │   ├── build_runtime.py\n1340: │           │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n1341: │           │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n1342: │           │   └── status_runtime.py\n1343: │           ├── services/\n1344: │           │   ├── docker_service.py\n1345: │           │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n1346: │           │   └── metadata_service.py\n1347: │           └── models/\n1348: │               └── pack_models.py\n1349: │\n1350: ├── test/\n1351: │   ├── unit/                      # Unit tests\n1352: │   ├── integration/               # Integration tests\n1353: │   └── e2e/                       # End-to-end tests\n1354: │\n1355: ├── docs/\n1356: │   └── docs/\n1357: │       └── architecture/\n1358: │           ├── overview.md\n1359: │           ├── components.md\n1360: │           ├── data-flow.md\n1361: │           ├── security.md\n1362: │           └── design.md          # This document\n1363: │\n1364: └── deployment/\n1365:     ├── helm/\n1366:     │   └── agentcube/\n1367:     │       ├── Chart.yaml\n1368:     │       ├── values.yaml\n1369:     │       └── templates/\n1370:     └── k8s/\n1371:         ├── router-deployment.yaml\n1372:         ├── workload-deployment.yaml\n1373:         └── agentd-deployment.yaml\n1374: ```\n1375: \n1376: ## Regeneration\n1377: \n1378: ### Kubernetes Client\n1379: \n1380: ```bash\n1381: # Regenerate client-go\n1382: make gen-client\n1383: ```\n1384: \n1385: **Dependencies:**\n1386: - `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n1387: - `--with-watch` flag enabled\n1388: \n1389: ### Protocol Buffers (if applicable)\n1390: \n1391: ```bash\n1392: # Regenerate protobuf\n1393: make gen-proto\n1394: ```\n1395: \n1396: ### Documentation\n1397: \n1398: ```bash\n1399: # Build documentation site\n1400: cd docs && npm run build\n1401: ```\n1402: \n1403: ## Related Documents\n1404: \n1405: - [Architecture Overview](overview.md)\n1406: - [Component Details](components.md)\n1407: - [Data Flow](data-flow.md)\n1408: - [Security Model](security.md)\n1409: - [AR-005 Sandbox Processor Design](../../design.md#design-ar-005-sandbox-creation-processor)\n1410: - [AR-014 Valkey Storage Design](../../design.md#design-ar-014-valkey-storage-implementation)\n1411: - [AR-017 PicoD JWT Design](../../design.md#design-ar-017-picod-jwt-middleware)\n1412: - [AR-035 client-go Design](../../design.md#design-ar-035-client-go)\n\n(End of file - total 1412 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-043 AgentCube Technical Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the comprehensive technical implementation details for the AgentCube platform. It covers the system architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling strategies, and testing approaches for all core components.\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents that provisions isolated sandbox environments on demand, routes HTTP traffic through session-aware proxies, and manages the complete sandbox lifecycle.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Architecture\n\n```\n                                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                                    │   Client/SDK    │\n                                    │   (Python/Go)   │\n                                    └────────┬────────┘\n                                             │\n                                    ┌────────▼────────┐\n                                    │   Ingress/LB    │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/design.md","time":{"start":1775894923803,"end":1775894923843}}}}
