{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894945807,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b965ad5001k2eKIMdq7PHhhN","messageID":"msg_d7b96436a001B46gBiT0QbG53w","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_766c3efcea76454ebca8f024","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-043: 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `docs`  \n6: **Language:** Markdown  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Architecture design and API documentation for agentcube project\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-043.1: Architecture Documentation Structure\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide an `docs/architecture/` directory with architecture design documentation.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Architecture directory exists\n21: - **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n22: - **WHEN** the documentation structure is inspected\n23: - **THEN** `docs/architecture/` directory SHALL exist\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Architecture overview document\n26: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n27: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n28: - **THEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` SHALL provide system architecture overview\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Architecture overview contains system vision\n31: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n32: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL describe AgentCube's vision as Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Architecture overview contains layered diagram\n36: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n37: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL include ASCII or Mermaid diagram showing Client Layer, API Gateway, Session Routing, Workload Manager, Sandbox Orchestration, and State Storage\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Architecture overview contains component table\n41: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n42: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL include table listing Router, Workload Manager, Sandbox Manager, Store, and PicoD with their responsibilities and tech stack\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Architecture overview contains design decisions\n46: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/overview.md` exists\n47: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL document key design decisions: Kubernetes-native, session affinity, warm pool optimization, and isolated execution\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Core components design document\n51: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n52: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n53: - **THEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` SHALL provide detailed component designs\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Router component documentation\n56: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` exists\n57: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL document Router's responsibilities, architecture diagram, and key interfaces\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Workload Manager component documentation\n61: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` exists\n62: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL document Workload Manager's responsibilities, architecture diagram, and CRD watch mechanism\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Store component documentation\n66: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/components.md` exists\n67: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL document Store's responsibilities, Redis/Valkey integration, and architecture\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Data flow design document\n71: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n72: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n73: - **THEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` SHALL describe data flow and request processing\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session creation flow\n76: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n77: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL document the session creation flow: Client → Router → Store → Workload Manager → Sandbox Pod\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Request routing flow\n81: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n82: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n83: - **THEN** it SHALL document the request routing flow: Client → Router → Store → Backend URL lookup → Agent Pod\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Session expiration flow\n86: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n87: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n88: - **THEN** it SHALL document the session expiration flow: TTL expires → Redis key deleted → Keyspace notification → Workload Manager deletes sandbox\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Sandbox lifecycle states\n91: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` exists\n92: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n93: - **THEN** it SHALL document sandbox lifecycle states: Pending → Creating → Running → Idle → Terminating → Terminated\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Deployment architecture document\n96: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n97: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n98: - **THEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` SHALL describe deployment architectures\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Development environment deployment\n101: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` exists\n102: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL document Kind cluster deployment with agentcube-system namespace\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Production environment deployment\n106: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` exists\n107: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n108: - **THEN** it SHALL document multi-cluster production deployment with load balancer\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Resource configuration table\n111: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/deployment.md` exists\n112: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n113: - **THEN** it SHALL include resource configuration table with CPU/Memory requests and limits for Router, Workload Manager, Redis, and Sandbox Pod\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Security architecture document\n116: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/` directory exists\n117: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n118: - **THEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` SHALL describe security architecture\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Security boundary diagram\n121: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` exists\n122: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL include security boundary diagram showing External Network, API Gateway, Internal Network, and Sandbox Pod\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Authentication and authorization\n126: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` exists\n127: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL document authentication mechanisms: JWT Token, mTLS, RSA Key Pair for PicoD, and Kubernetes RBAC\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Sandbox security measures\n131: - **GIVEN** `docs/architecture/security.md` exists\n132: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n133: - **THEN** it SHALL document sandbox security: non-root user, read-only root FS, dropped capabilities, syscall restrictions, namespace isolation, and resource quotas\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ### REQ-043.2: API Documentation Structure\n138: \n139: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docs/api/` directory with API documentation for all core components.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: API directory exists\n142: - **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n143: - **WHEN** the documentation structure is inspected\n144: - **THEN** `docs/api/` directory SHALL exist\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: API README index\n147: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n148: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n149: - **THEN** `docs/api/README.md` SHALL provide API documentation index\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Router API documentation\n152: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n153: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n154: - **THEN** `docs/api/router.md` SHALL document Router API endpoints\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Router API endpoints documented\n157: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/router.md` exists\n158: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL document endpoints: POST /api/v1/sessions, GET /api/v1/sessions/:sessionID, DELETE /api/v1/sessions/:sessionID\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Router API request/response examples\n162: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/router.md` exists\n163: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL include JSON request/response examples for each endpoint\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Router API client example\n167: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/router.md` exists\n168: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL include Python SDK client usage example\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Workload Manager API documentation\n172: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n173: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n174: - **THEN** `docs/api/workload-manager.md` SHALL document Workload Manager API endpoints\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Workload Manager API endpoints documented\n177: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/workload-manager.md` exists\n178: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n179: - **THEN** it SHALL document endpoints: POST /api/v1/workloads, GET /api/v1/workloads/:name, PATCH /api/v1/workloads/:name/scale, DELETE /api/v1/workloads/:name\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Workload Manager API request/response examples\n182: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/workload-manager.md` exists\n183: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL include JSON request/response examples for each endpoint\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Store API documentation\n187: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n188: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n189: - **THEN** `docs/api/store.md` SHALL document Store interface\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Store interface methods\n192: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/store.md` exists\n193: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n194: - **THEN** it SHALL document interface methods: Set, Get, Delete, Exists, Watch with signatures\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Store event types\n197: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/store.md` exists\n198: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n199: - **THEN** it SHALL document Event struct and EventType constants (EventSet, EventDelete)\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Store usage example\n202: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/store.md` exists\n203: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL include Go usage example demonstrating Set, Get, and Watch operations\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Sandbox Manager API documentation\n207: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n208: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n209: - **THEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` SHALL document Sandbox Manager interface\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Sandbox Manager interface methods\n212: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` exists\n213: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n214: - **THEN** it SHALL document interface methods: Create, Update, Delete, Get, List with signatures\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: WarmPool Manager interface\n217: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` exists\n218: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL document WarmPoolManager interface with Precreate, Acquire, and Refill methods\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Sandbox Manager usage example\n222: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` exists\n223: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL include Go usage example demonstrating Create and WarmPool.Acquire operations\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: PicoD API documentation\n227: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/` directory exists\n228: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n229: - **THEN** `docs/api/picod.md` SHALL document PicoD API\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: PicoD interface methods\n232: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n233: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n234: - **THEN** it SHALL document interface methods: Run, Start, RunWithStreaming with signatures\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: PicoD Command struct\n237: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n238: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n239: - **THEN** it SHALL document Command struct with Path, Args, Env, Dir, and Stdin fields\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: PicoD CommandResult struct\n242: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n243: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n244: - **THEN** it SHALL document CommandResult struct with ExitCode, Stdout, Stderr, Duration, OOMKilled, and Timeout fields\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: PicoD usage example\n247: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n248: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n249: - **THEN** it SHALL include Go usage example demonstrating Run command execution\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: PicoD HTTP endpoints\n252: - **GIVEN** `docs/api/picod.md` exists\n253: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n254: - **THEN** it SHALL document HTTP endpoints: POST /execute, GET /health with request/response examples\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ### REQ-043.3: Design Specifications Structure\n259: \n260: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `docs/design/` directory with coding standards and design specifications.\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Design directory exists\n263: - **GIVEN** the agentcube repository root\n264: - **WHEN** the documentation structure is inspected\n265: - **THEN** `docs/design/` directory SHALL exist\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Coding standards document\n268: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/` directory exists\n269: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n270: - **THEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` SHALL provide coding standards\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Go code formatting standards\n273: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n274: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL specify: use gofmt/goimports, 120 character line width, tab indentation\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Go naming standards\n278: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n279: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n280: - **THEN** it SHALL specify: lowercase package names, exported identifiers with capital first letter, private identifiers with lowercase first letter\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Error handling standards\n283: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n284: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n285: - **THEN** it SHALL specify: use errors.Wrap for context, lowercase error messages, never ignore errors\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Test standards\n288: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/coding-standards.md` exists\n289: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL specify: `*_test.go` files, `TestXxx` function names, table-driven tests preferred\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Naming conventions document\n293: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/` directory exists\n294: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n295: - **THEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` SHALL provide naming conventions\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: CRD naming conventions\n298: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` exists\n299: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n300: - **THEN** it SHALL specify: plural form (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters), short names (ar, ci)\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: API Group naming conventions\n303: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` exists\n304: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n305: - **THEN** it SHALL specify format: `<resource>.agentcube.volcano.sh`, versions: v1alpha1, v1beta1, v1\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Environment variable naming\n308: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` exists\n309: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n310: - **THEN** it SHALL specify: AGENTCUBE_ prefix, uppercase (AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_PORT)\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Error handling specification document\n313: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/` directory exists\n314: - **WHEN** documentation content is inspected\n315: - **THEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` SHALL provide error handling specification\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: Error struct definition\n318: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` exists\n319: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n320: - **THEN** it SHALL document Error struct with Code, Message, and Cause fields\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: Error codes table\n323: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` exists\n324: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n325: - **THEN** it SHALL include error codes table: ERR_INVALID_INPUT, ERR_NOT_FOUND, ERR_ALREADY_EXISTS, ERR_TIMEOUT, ERR_INTERNAL\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Error handling pattern\n328: - **GIVEN** `docs/design/error-handling.md` exists\n329: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n330: - **THEN** it SHALL include Go code example: `return nil, errors.Wrap(err, \"failed to create sandbox\")`\n331: \n332: ---\n333: \n334: ### REQ-043.4: Documentation Integration\n335: \n336: **Requirement:** The system SHALL integrate architecture and API documentation with the AR-042 Docusaurus documentation site.\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Documentation README exists\n339: - **GIVEN** `docs/` directory exists\n340: - **WHEN** documentation structure is inspected\n341: - **THEN** `docs/README.md` SHALL exist with documentation guide\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Documentation structure explanation\n344: - **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n345: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n346: - **THEN** it SHALL explain the relationship between architecture/, api/, design/ directories\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: AR-042 and AR-043 relationship\n349: - **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n350: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n351: - **THEN** it SHALL explain that AR-043 content serves as source material for AR-042 Docusaurus site\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Documentation reader guidance\n354: - **GIVEN** `docs/README.md` exists\n355: - **WHEN** content is evaluated\n356: - **THEN** it SHALL provide guidance for different readers: developers, architects, operators\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Mermaid diagram support\n359: - **GIVEN** documentation files exist\n360: - **WHEN** diagrams are evaluated\n361: - **THEN** architecture and data flow documents SHALL use Mermaid for diagrams where applicable\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: Cross-references between documents\n364: - **GIVEN** documentation files exist\n365: - **WHEN** links are evaluated\n366: - **THEN** documents SHALL include proper relative links to related documents within the docs/ directory\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ### REQ-043.5: Documentation Quality\n371: \n372: **Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain high-quality documentation that is accurate, consistent, and up-to-date.\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: API accuracy verification\n375: - **GIVEN** API documentation exists\n376: - **WHEN** code review is conducted\n377: - **THEN** API documentation SHALL accurately reflect the actual Go interface definitions in pkg/\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Architecture accuracy verification\n380: - **GIVEN** architecture documentation exists\n381: - **WHEN** architecture review is conducted\n382: - **THEN** architecture documentation SHALL accurately reflect the actual system design\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: Consistent terminology\n385: - **GIVEN** all documentation files exist\n386: - **WHEN** terminology is evaluated across documents\n387: - **THEN** terminology SHALL be consistent: Router, Workload Manager, Sandbox Manager, Store, PicoD\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: Consistent formatting\n390: - **GIVEN** all documentation files exist\n391: - **WHEN** formatting is evaluated\n392: - **THEN** all documents SHALL use consistent Markdown formatting, heading levels, and code block styles\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Example code correctness\n395: - **GIVEN** documentation contains code examples\n396: - **WHEN** examples are evaluated\n397: - **THEN** Go and Python code examples SHALL be syntactically correct and follow project conventions\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Diagram clarity\n400: - **GIVEN** documentation contains diagrams\n401: - **WHEN** diagrams are evaluated\n402: - **THEN** ASCII and Mermaid diagrams SHALL be clear and properly formatted\n403: \n404: ---\n405: \n406: ## Data Types\n407: \n408: ```typescript\n409: // Documentation file structure\n410: interface ArchitectureDoc {\n411:   overview: {\n412:     vision: string;\n413:     layers: string[];\n414:     components: ComponentInfo[];\n415:     designDecisions: string[];\n416:   };\n417:   components: {\n418:     router: ComponentDesign;\n419:     workloadManager: ComponentDesign;\n420:     store: ComponentDesign;\n421:   };\n422:   dataFlow: {\n423:     sessionCreation: FlowStep[];\n424:     requestRouting: FlowStep[];\n425:     sessionExpiration: FlowStep[];\n426:     sandboxLifecycle: string[];\n427:   };\n428:   deployment: {\n429:     development: DeploymentConfig;\n430:     production: DeploymentConfig;\n431:     resources: ResourceConfig[];\n432:   };\n433:   security: {\n434:     boundaries: string[];\n435:     auth: AuthMechanism[];\n436:     sandboxSecurity: string[];\n437:   };\n438: }\n439: \n440: interface APIDoc {\n441:   router: {\n442:     endpoints: Endpoint[];\n443:     clientExample: string;\n444:   };\n445:   workloadManager: {\n446:     endpoints: Endpoint[];\n447:   };\n448:   store: {\n449:     interface: InterfaceMethod[];\n450:     events: EventType[];\n451:     usageExample: string;\n452:   };\n453:   sandboxManager: {\n454:     interface: InterfaceMethod[];\n455:     warmPool: WarmPoolInterface;\n456:     usageExample: string;\n457:   };\n458:   picod: {\n459:     interface: InterfaceMethod[];\n460:     structs: StructDefinition[];\n461:     httpEndpoints: Endpoint[];\n462:     usageExample: string;\n463:   };\n464: }\n465: \n466: interface DesignSpec {\n467:   codingStandards: {\n468:     formatting: FormattingRule[];\n469:     naming: NamingRule[];\n470:     errorHandling: ErrorHandlingRule[];\n471:     testing: TestingRule[];\n472:   };\n473:   namingConventions: {\n474:     crd: CRDNaming;\n475:     apiGroup: string;\n476:     envVars: string;\n477:   };\n478:   errorHandling: {\n479:     errorStruct: ErrorDefinition;\n480:     errorCodes: ErrorCode[];\n481:     pattern: string;\n482:   };\n483: }\n484: ```\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## File Structure\n489: \n490: ```\n491: agentcube/\n492: └── docs/\n493:     ├── README.md                          # Documentation guide and index\n494:     ├── architecture/                      # Architecture design documentation\n495:     │   ├── overview.md                    # System architecture overview\n496:     │   ├── components.md                  # Core component designs\n497:     │   ├── data-flow.md                   # Data flow and request processing\n498:     │   ├── deployment.md                  # Deployment architectures\n499:     │   └── security.md                    # Security architecture\n500:     ├── api/                               # API documentation\n501:     │   ├── README.md                      # API documentation index\n502:     │   ├── router.md                      # Router API reference\n503:     │   ├── workload-manager.md            # Workload Manager API reference\n504:     │   ├── store.md                       # Store API reference\n505:     │   ├── sandbox-manager.md             # Sandbox Manager API reference\n506:     │   └── picod.md                       # PicoD API reference\n507:     └── design/                            # Design specifications\n508:         ├── coding-standards.md            # Go coding standards\n509:         ├── naming-conventions.md          # Naming conventions\n510:         └── error-handling.md              # Error handling specification\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## Documentation Standards\n516: \n517: | Element | Standard | Required |\n518: |---------|----------|----------|\n519: | File format | Markdown | Yes |\n520: | Heading style | ATX (#) | Yes |\n521: | Code blocks | Fenced with language | Yes |\n522: | Diagrams | ASCII or Mermaid | Yes (where applicable) |\n523: | API examples | JSON/Go/Python | Yes |\n524: | Cross-references | Relative links | Yes |\n525: | Line width | 120 characters max | Recommended |\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## Content Requirements\n530: \n531: ### Architecture Documents\n532: \n533: | Document | Required Sections | Diagrams | Code Examples |\n534: |----------|------------------|----------|---------------|\n535: | overview.md | Vision, Layers, Components, Design Decisions | Layered architecture | No |\n536: | components.md | Router, Workload Manager, Store | Component architecture | Interface definitions |\n537: | data-flow.md | Session creation, Routing, Expiration, Lifecycle | Flow diagrams | No |\n538: | deployment.md | Dev env, Prod env, Resources | Deployment topology | Resource config |\n539: | security.md | Boundaries, Auth, Sandbox | Security boundary | No |\n540: \n541: ### API Documents\n542: \n543: | Document | Required Sections | Request/Response | Client Examples |\n544: |----------|------------------|------------------|-----------------|\n545: | router.md | Endpoints, Examples | JSON | Python SDK |\n546: | workload-manager.md | Endpoints, Examples | JSON | No |\n547: | store.md | Interface, Events, Examples | No | Go |\n548: | sandbox-manager.md | Interface, WarmPool, Examples | No | Go |\n549: | picod.md | Interface, Structs, HTTP, Examples | JSON | Go |\n550: \n551: ### Design Documents\n552: \n553: | Document | Required Sections | Code Examples |\n554: |----------|------------------|---------------|\n555: | coding-standards.md | Formatting, Naming, Errors, Testing | Yes |\n556: | naming-conventions.md | CRD, API Group, Env Vars | No |\n557: | error-handling.md | Error struct, Codes, Pattern | Yes |\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ## Acceptance Checklist\n562: \n563: ### Architecture Documentation\n564: - [ ] `docs/architecture/` — Directory exists\n565: - [ ] `docs/architecture/overview.md` — Contains system vision and layered architecture diagram\n566: - [ ] `docs/architecture/overview.md` — Contains component table with responsibilities\n567: - [ ] `docs/architecture/overview.md` — Documents key design decisions\n568: - [ ] `docs/architecture/components.md` — Documents Router with interface\n569: - [ ] `docs/architecture/components.md` — Documents Workload Manager with CRD watch\n570: - [ ] `docs/architecture/components.md` — Documents Store with Redis integration\n571: - [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents session creation flow\n572: - [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents request routing flow\n573: - [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents session expiration flow\n574: - [ ] `docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — Documents sandbox lifecycle states\n575: - [ ] `docs/architecture/deployment.md` — Documents Kind development deployment\n576: - [ ] `docs/architecture/deployment.md` — Documents multi-cluster production deployment\n577: - [ ] `docs/architecture/deployment.md` — Contains resource configuration table\n578: - [ ] `docs/architecture/security.md` — Contains security boundary diagram\n579: - [ ] `docs/architecture/security.md` — Documents authentication mechanisms\n580: - [ ] `docs/architecture/security.md` — Documents sandbox security measures\n581: \n582: ### API Documentation\n583: - [ ] `docs/api/` — Directory exists\n584: - [ ] `docs/api/README.md` — API documentation index exists\n585: - [ ] `docs/api/router.md` — Documents POST/GET/DELETE /api/v1/sessions endpoints\n586: - [ ] `docs/api/router.md` — Contains JSON request/response examples\n587: - [ ] `docs/api/router.md` — Contains Python SDK usage example\n588: - [ ] `docs/api/workload-manager.md` — Documents workload CRUD and scale endpoints\n589: - [ ] `docs/api/workload-manager.md` — Contains JSON request/response examples\n590: - [ ] `docs/api/store.md` — Documents Store interface with Set/Get/Delete/Exists/Watch\n591: - [ ] `docs/api/store.md` — Documents Event struct and EventType constants\n592: - [ ] `docs/api/store.md` — Contains Go usage example\n593: - [ ] `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` — Documents SandboxManager interface\n594: - [ ] `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` — Documents WarmPoolManager interface\n595: - [ ] `docs/api/sandbox-manager.md` — Contains Go usage example\n596: - [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Documents PicoD interface with Run/Start/RunWithStreaming\n597: - [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Documents Command and CommandResult structs\n598: - [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Contains Go usage example\n599: - [ ] `docs/api/picod.md` — Documents POST /execute and GET /health HTTP endpoints\n600: \n601: ### Design Specifications\n602: - [ ] `docs/design/` — Directory exists\n603: - [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents Go formatting standards\n604: - [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents naming standards\n605: - [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents error handling standards\n606: - [ ] `docs/design/coding-standards.md` — Documents testing standards\n607: - [ ] `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` — Documents CRD naming conventions\n608: - [ ] `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` — Documents API Group format\n609: - [ ] `docs/design/naming-conventions.md` — Documents environment variable naming\n610: - [ ] `docs/design/error-handling.md` — Documents Error struct\n611: - [ ] `docs/design/error-handling.md` — Documents error codes table\n612: - [ ] `docs/design/error-handling.md` — Documents error handling pattern\n613: \n614: ### Documentation Quality\n615: - [ ] `docs/README.md` — Documentation guide exists\n616: - [ ] `docs/README.md` — Explains directory structure\n617: - [ ] `docs/README.md` — Explains AR-042 and AR-043 relationship\n618: - [ ] Cross-references — Documents link to each other correctly\n619: - [ ] Terminology — Consistent across all documents\n620: - [ ] Formatting — Consistent Markdown style\n621: - [ ] Code examples — Syntactically correct\n622: - [ ] Diagrams — Clear and properly formatted\n623: - [ ] API accuracy — Matches actual Go interfaces in pkg/\n624: - [ ] Architecture accuracy — Matches actual system design\n625: \n626: ---\n627: \n628: ## Open Questions\n629: \n630: 1. Should API documentation be auto-generated from Go code comments using a tool like swag or gomarkdoc?\n631: 2. Should we integrate with OpenAPI/Swagger for interactive API testing?\n632: 3. Should architecture diagrams use a specific tool (Draw.io, Lucidchart) instead of ASCII/Mermaid?\n633: 4. Should we add versioning to documentation to track changes across releases?\n634: 5. Should we create a separate CHANGELOG.md for documentation updates?\n635: 6. Should API documentation include error response schemas for each endpoint?\n636: 7. Should we add performance benchmarks and SLA documentation?\n637: 8. Should we create troubleshooting guides as part of the architecture documentation?\n638: 9. Should we document migration paths between different versions?\n639: 10. Should we add glossary of terms for new team members?\n\n(End of file - total 639 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-043: 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `docs`  \n**Language:** Markdown  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Architecture design and API documentation for agentcube project\n\n**Base Specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-043.1: Architecture Documentation Structure\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide an `docs/architecture/` directory with architecture design documentation.\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture directory exists","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775894945796,"end":1775894945805}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894945818,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b96557d001dXgIlQllxCJ9O2","messageID":"msg_d7b96436a001B46gBiT0QbG53w","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_051fbbdd2ca54b0bbedec104","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: overview\n3: title: Architecture Overview\n4: slug: /architecture/overview\n5: sidebar_label: Overview\n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## System Architecture\n9: \n10: AgentCube follows a microservices architecture built on Kubernetes primitives. The system consists of several key components that work together to provide sandbox orchestration capabilities.\n11: \n12: ```\n13:                                     ┌─────────────────┐\n14:                                     │   Client/SDK    │\n15:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n16:                                              │\n17:                                     ┌────────▼────────┐\n18:                                     │   Ingress/LB    │\n19:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n20:                                              │\n21:                                     ┌────────▼────────┐\n22:                                     │   Router (:8080)│◄───────┐\n23:                                     └────────┬────────┘        │\n24:                                              │                 │\n25:                           ┌──────────────────┼──────────────────┤\n26:                           │                  │                  │\n27:                 ┌─────────▼─────────┐ ┌──────▼──────┐ ┌────────▼────────┐\n28:                 │  Workload Manager  │ │Session Store│ │    Agentd       │\n29:                 │   (:8081)          │ │   (Redis)   │ │  (Cleanup)      │\n30:                 └─────────┬─────────┘ └─────────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n31:                           │\n32:                           │ K8s API\n33:                           ▼\n34:                 ┌─────────────────────┐\n35:                 │   Sandbox Pods      │\n36:                 │  ┌─────┐ ┌─────┐   │\n37:                 │  │Pod 1│ │Pod 2│...│\n38:                 │  └─────┘ └─────┘   │\n39:                 └─────────────────────┘\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ## Core Components\n43: \n44: ### 1. Router\n45: \n46: The Router is the entry point for all client requests. It handles:\n47: \n48: - **Session Routing**: Routes requests to appropriate sandbox instances based on session IDs\n49: - **Load Balancing**: Distributes traffic across available sandbox pods\n50: - **Authentication**: Validates JWT tokens and Kubernetes service account tokens\n51: - **Rate Limiting**: Enforces rate limits per client/session\n52: \n53: ### 2. Workload Manager\n54: \n55: The Workload Manager controls the sandbox lifecycle:\n56: \n57: - **Sandbox Provisioning**: Creates new sandbox pods on demand\n58: - **Resource Management**: Allocates and monitors resource usage\n59: - **Health Monitoring**: Tracks sandbox health and availability\n60: - **Scaling**: Auto-scales based on demand\n61: \n62: ### 3. Session Store (Redis)\n63: \n64: Redis provides durable session state management:\n65: \n66: - **Session Metadata**: Stores session configuration and state\n67: - **Routing Tables**: Maps sessions to sandbox instances\n68: - **Rate Limit Counters**: Tracks request rates per client\n69: - **Temporary Storage**: Caches frequently accessed data\n70: \n71: ### 4. Agent Daemon (Agentd)\n72: \n73: Agentd handles background maintenance tasks:\n74: \n75: - **Idle Cleanup**: Terminates sandboxes that have been idle beyond threshold\n76: - **Resource Reclamation**: Frees up resources from terminated sandboxes\n77: - **Health Checks**: Periodically verifies sandbox health\n78: \n79: ## Kubernetes Resources\n80: \n81: ### Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs)\n82: \n83: AgentCube defines the following CRDs:\n84: \n85: - **Sandbox**: Represents an individual sandbox instance\n86: - **SandboxConfig**: Configuration templates for sandboxes\n87: - **Session**: Tracks active user sessions\n88: - **Route**: Defines custom routing rules\n89: \n90: ### Standard Resources\n91: \n92: - **Deployments**: For stateless components (Router, Workload Manager)\n93: - **StatefulSets**: For stateful components (Redis)\n94: - **Services**: For internal and external networking\n95: - **ConfigMaps/Secrets**: For configuration management\n96: \n97: ## Data Flow\n98: \n99: 1. Client sends request to Router with session ID\n100: 2. Router validates authentication and checks rate limits\n101: 3. Router queries Redis for session-to-sandbox mapping\n102: 4. Router forwards request to appropriate sandbox pod\n103: 5. Sandbox processes request and returns response\n104: 6. Response flows back through Router to client\n105: \n106: ## Security Model\n107: \n108: - **Network Isolation**: Sandboxes run in isolated network namespaces\n109: - **Resource Limits**: CPU and memory limits prevent resource exhaustion\n110: - **RBAC**: Fine-grained Kubernetes permissions\n111: - **Authentication**: JWT and Kubernetes token-based auth\n112: - **Encryption**: TLS for all external communications\n\n(End of file - total 112 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: overview\ntitle: Architecture Overview\nslug: /architecture/overview\nsidebar_label: Overview\n---\n\n## System Architecture\n\nAgentCube follows a microservices architecture built on Kubernetes primitives. The system consists of several key components that work together to provide sandbox orchestration capabilities.\n\n```\n                                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                                    │   Client/SDK    │\n                                    └────────┬────────┘\n                                             │\n                                    ┌────────▼────────┐\n                                    │   Ingress/LB    │\n                                    └────────┬────────┘\n                                             │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md","time":{"start":1775894945794,"end":1775894945817}}}}
