{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894955470,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9680d5001RMViNchELayRLc","messageID":"msg_d7b966055001mfkMSmkde04sLY","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7eb3717b39e0466e85e9ed4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: components\n3: title: Component Details\n4: slug: /architecture/components\n5: sidebar_label: Components\n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Router\n9: \n10: ### Purpose\n11: \n12: The Router serves as the central traffic controller for AgentCube, handling all incoming requests and routing them to the appropriate sandbox instances.\n13: \n14: ### Responsibilities\n15: \n16: - **Request Routing**: Maps incoming requests to sandbox pods based on session metadata\n17: - **Authentication & Authorization**: Validates credentials using JWT or Kubernetes tokens\n18: - **Rate Limiting**: Enforces per-client rate limits using token bucket algorithm\n19: - **Session Management**: Maintains session state and handles session lifecycle\n20: - **Health Checking**: Monitors sandbox availability and removes unhealthy instances\n21: \n22: ### API Endpoints\n23: \n24: | Method | Endpoint | Description |\n25: |--------|----------|-------------|\n26: | GET | `/healthz` | Liveness probe endpoint |\n27: | GET | `/ready` | Readiness probe endpoint |\n28: | POST | `/api/v1/sessions` | Create new session |\n29: | GET | `/api/v1/sessions/{id}` | Get session details |\n30: | DELETE | `/api/v1/sessions/{id}` | Terminate session |\n31: | GET | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | List available sandboxes |\n32: | POST | `/api/v1/proxy/{sandboxId}/*` | Proxy to sandbox |\n33: \n34: ### Configuration\n35: \n36: ```yaml\n37: router:\n38:   port: 8080\n39:   sessionTimeout: 3600s\n40:   maxSessionsPerClient: 10\n41:   rateLimit:\n42:     enabled: true\n43:     requestsPerSecond: 100\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ## Workload Manager\n47: \n48: ### Purpose\n49: \n50: The Workload Manager is responsible for the complete lifecycle of sandbox pods, from creation through termination.\n51: \n52: ### Responsibilities\n53: \n54: - **Pod Creation**: Provisions new sandbox pods based on configuration\n55: - **Resource Allocation**: Assigns CPU, memory, and storage to sandboxes\n56: - **Scheduling**: Places sandboxes on appropriate nodes\n57: - **Monitoring**: Tracks resource usage and health status\n58: - **Auto-scaling**: Scales sandbox count based on demand\n59: \n60: ### Scheduling Strategy\n61: \n62: The Workload Manager uses a multi-factor scheduling algorithm:\n63: \n64: 1. **Resource Availability**: Checks node capacity for requested resources\n65: 2. **Affinity Rules**: Respects pod affinity/anti-affinity configurations\n66: 3. **Load Balancing**: Distributes sandboxes across nodes\n67: 4. **Priority**: Honors pod priority classes\n68: \n69: ### Sandbox Lifecycle States\n70: \n71: ```\n72: PENDING → PROVISIONING → RUNNING → TERMINATING → TERMINATED\n73:               ↓              ↓\n74:            FAILED       ERROR\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ## Session Store (Redis)\n78: \n79: ### Purpose\n80: \n81: Redis provides fast, durable storage for session state and routing information.\n82: \n83: ### Data Structures\n84: \n85: | Key Pattern | Type | Description |\n86: |-------------|------|-------------|\n87: | `session:{id}` | Hash | Session metadata |\n88: | `session:{id}:route` | String | Active sandbox ID |\n89: | `client:{id}:sessions` | Set | Client's session IDs |\n90: | `ratelimit:{client}` | String | Rate limit counter |\n91: | `sandbox:{id}:status` | String | Sandbox health status |\n92: \n93: ### TTL Configuration\n94: \n95: Session data has automatic expiration:\n96: \n97: - Active sessions: 1 hour (refreshable)\n98: - Rate limit counters: 1 second (sliding window)\n99: - Health status: 30 seconds\n100: \n101: ## Agent Daemon (Agentd)\n102: \n103: ### Purpose\n104: \n105: Agentd performs background maintenance to optimize resource usage.\n106: \n107: ### Cleanup Policies\n108: \n109: | Policy | Default | Description |\n110: |--------|---------|-------------|\n111: | `idleTimeout` | 300s | Terminate sandboxes idle for this duration |\n112: | `cleanupInterval` | 60s | How often to run cleanup cycle |\n113: | `gracePeriod` | 30s | Time to wait before force-terminating |\n114: \n115: ### Cleanup Algorithm\n116: \n117: ```\n118: for each sandbox:\n119:   if sandbox.idleTime > idleTimeout:\n120:     mark sandbox for termination\n121:     wait gracePeriod\n122:     if sandbox still idle:\n123:       terminate sandbox\n124:       release resources\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ## Picod Daemon (Optional)\n128: \n129: ### Purpose\n130: \n131: Picod is an optional sidecar daemon that runs inside sandbox pods for enhanced control.\n132: \n133: ### Features\n134: \n135: - **Process Management**: Monitor and control processes inside the sandbox\n136: - **Network Policy**: Enforce network egress restrictions\n137: - **Metrics Collection**: Gather detailed resource usage metrics\n138: - **Command Execution**: Execute commands inside the sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: components\ntitle: Component Details\nslug: /architecture/components\nsidebar_label: Components\n---\n\n## Router\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe Router serves as the central traffic controller for AgentCube, handling all incoming requests and routing them to the appropriate sandbox instances.\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n- **Request Routing**: Maps incoming requests to sandbox pods based on session metadata\n- **Authentication & Authorization**: Validates credentials using JWT or Kubernetes tokens\n- **Rate Limiting**: Enforces per-client rate limits using token bucket algorithm\n- **Session Management**: Maintains session state and handles session lifecycle\n- **Health Checking**: Monitors sandbox availability and removes unhealthy instances","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md","time":{"start":1775894955436,"end":1775894955467}}}}
