{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894960654,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b969064001SIhrWjfpdOG28D","messageID":"msg_d7b9685fe001td7XJr5dhdrxEI","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2efa9bc276d840109dc1a11b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: data-flow\n3: title: Data Flow\n4: slug: /architecture/data-flow\n5: sidebar_label: Data Flow\n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Request Flow\n9: \n10: This document describes how requests flow through the AgentCube system.\n11: \n12: ### Session Creation Flow\n13: \n14: ```\n15: Client                    Router                Redis              Workload Manager\n16:   │                        │                     │                       │\n17:   │──Create Session──────▶│                     │                       │\n18:   │                        │                     │                       │\n19:   │                        │────Get Config─────▶│                       │\n20:   │                        │◄────Config─────────│                       │\n21:   │                        │                     │                       │\n22:   │                        │────Request Sandbox─────────────────────────▶│\n23:   │                        │                     │                       │\n24:   │                        │                     │                  [Create Pod]\n25:   │                        │                     │                       │\n26:   │                        │◄───────Pod Created──────────────────────────│\n27:   │                        │                     │                       │\n28:   │                        │────Store Mapping──▶│                       │\n29:   │                        │◄──────OK───────────│                       │\n30:   │                        │                     │                       │\n31:   │◄────Session ID────────│                     │                       │\n32:   │                        │                     │                       │\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### Request Execution Flow\n36: \n37: ```\n38: Client                    Router                Redis              Sandbox Pod\n39:   │                        │                     │                     │\n40:   │──Execute Request─────▶│                     │                     │\n41:   │   (with Session ID)    │                     │                     │\n42:   │                        │                     │                     │\n43:   │                        │────Get Route──────▶│                     │\n44:   │                        │◄──Sandbox ID───────│                     │\n45:   │                        │                     │                     │\n46:   │                        │────Forward Request───────────────────────▶│\n47:   │                        │                     │                     │\n48:   │                        │                     │               [Process]\n49:   │                        │                     │                     │\n50:   │                        │◄─────Response─────────────────────────────│\n51:   │                        │                     │                     │\n52:   │◄───────Response────────│                     │                     │\n53:   │                        │                     │                     │\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Idle Cleanup Flow\n57: \n58: ```\n59: Timer              Agentd               Redis           Workload Manager        Sandbox\n60:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n61:   │[Every 60s]      │                     │                    │                   │\n62:   │────────────────▶│                     │                    │                   │\n63:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n64:   │                 │────List Sessions──▶│                    │                   │\n65:   │                 │◄────All Sessions───│                    │                   │\n66:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n67:   │                 │────Check Idle Time─│                    │                   │\n68:   │                 │  (per session)     │                    │                   │\n69:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n70:   │                 │[Idle > Threshold]  │                    │                   │\n71:   │                 │────────────────────────────────────────▶│                   │\n72:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n73:   │                 │                     │                    │[Terminate Pod]    │\n74:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n75:   │                 │◄──────Terminated─────────────────────────│                   │\n76:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n77:   │                 │────Delete Session──▶│                    │                   │\n78:   │                 │                     │                    │                   │\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ## State Management\n82: \n83: ### Session State Machine\n84: \n85: ```\n86:                   ┌──────────────┐\n87:                   │   CREATED    │\n88:                   └──────┬───────┘\n89:                          │\n90:                          │ Assignment\n91:                          ▼\n92:                   ┌──────────────┐\n93:                   │   ASSIGNED   │───────────┐\n94:                   └──────┬───────┘           │\n95:                          │                   │ Sandbox\n96:                          │ Active            │ Failed\n97:                          ▼                   │\n98:                   ┌──────────────┐           │\n99:                   │    ACTIVE    │◄──────────┘\n100:                   └──────┬───────┘\n101:                          │\n102:                          │ Idle Timeout\n103:                          ▼\n104:                   ┌──────────────┐\n105:                   │    IDLE      │\n106:                   └──────┬───────┘\n107:                          │\n108:                          │ Cleanup\n109:                          ▼\n110:                   ┌──────────────┐\n111:                   │ TERMINATED   │\n112:                   └──────────────┘\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Sandbox State Machine\n116: \n117: ```\n118:                   ┌──────────────┐\n119:                   │   PENDING    │\n120:                   └──────┬───────┘\n121:                          │\n122:                          │ Scheduling\n123:                          ▼\n124:                   ┌──────────────┐\n125:                   │ PROVISIONING │\n126:                   └──────┬───────┘\n127:                          │\n128:                          │ Pod Running\n129:                          ▼\n130:                   ┌──────────────┐\n131:                   │   RUNNING    │───────────┐\n132:                   └──────┬───────┘           │\n133:                          │                   │ Error\n134:                          │ Terminate         │\n135:                          ▼                   ▼\n136:                   ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐\n137:                   │ TERMINATING  │    │    ERROR     │\n138:                   └──────┬───────┘    └──────────────┘\n139:                          │\n140:                          │ Pod Deleted\n141:                          ▼\n142:                   ┌──────────────┐\n143:                   │ TERMINATED   │\n144:                   └──────────────┘\n145: ```\n146: \n147: ## Data Persistence\n148: \n149: ### Redis Key Structure\n150: \n151: ```\n152: session:{id}              Hash     Session metadata\n153:   - client_id: string\n154:   - created_at: timestamp\n155:   - last_active: timestamp\n156:   - sandbox_id: string\n157:   - config: JSON\n158: \n159: session:{id}:route        String   Active sandbox ID\n160: \n161: client:{id}:sessions      Set      Client's session IDs\n162: \n163: sandbox:{id}:status       String   Current status\n164: sandbox:{id}:metrics      Hash     Resource usage\n165: \n166: ratelimit:{client}        String   Request count\n167: ratelimit:{client}:ts     String   Window start time\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Cache Invalidation\n171: \n172: - Session data refreshed on each request (TTL reset)\n173: - Sandbox status updated every 10 seconds\n174: - Rate limit counters reset every second\n\n(End of file - total 174 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: data-flow\ntitle: Data Flow\nslug: /architecture/data-flow\nsidebar_label: Data Flow\n---\n\n## Request Flow\n\nThis document describes how requests flow through the AgentCube system.\n\n### Session Creation Flow\n\n```\nClient                    Router                Redis              Workload Manager\n  │                        │                     │                       │\n  │──Create Session──────▶│                     │                       │\n  │                        │                     │                       │\n  │                        │────Get Config─────▶│                       │\n  │                        │◄────Config─────────│                       │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md","time":{"start":1775894960636,"end":1775894960652}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894960658,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b969530001GajJ0Zcgy1J76o","messageID":"msg_d7b9685fe001td7XJr5dhdrxEI","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_34ff0492ba774f7dbfce5e1e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/security.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/security.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: security\n3: title: Security Architecture\n4: slug: /architecture/security\n5: sidebar_label: Security\n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Security Overview\n9: \n10: AgentCube implements defense-in-depth security with multiple layers of protection:\n11: \n12: 1. **Authentication** - Verify identity of clients\n13: 2. **Authorization** - Control access to resources\n14: 3. **Isolation** - Prevent cross-sandbox interference\n15: 4. **Encryption** - Protect data in transit\n16: 5. **Auditing** - Track all operations\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: ### JWT Authentication\n21: \n22: AgentCube supports JWT RS256 token-based authentication:\n23: \n24: ```yaml\n25: auth:\n26:   jwt:\n27:     enabled: true\n28:     publicKey: |\n29:       -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n30:       MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n31:       -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n32:     algorithm: RS256\n33:     issuer: agentcube\n34:     audiences:\n35:       - agentcube-api\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ### Kubernetes Token Review\n39: \n40: For Kubernetes-native authentication:\n41: \n42: ```yaml\n43: auth:\n44:   kubernetes:\n45:     enabled: true\n46:     serviceAccount: agentcube-service\n47:     audiences:\n48:       - agentcube-api\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Token Format\n52: \n53: ```json\n54: {\n55:   \"sub\": \"user-123\",\n56:   \"iss\": \"agentcube\",\n57:   \"aud\": \"agentcube-api\",\n58:   \"exp\": 1700000000,\n59:   \"iat\": 1699996400,\n60:   \"permissions\": [\"sandbox:create\", \"sandbox:read\", \"sandbox:delete\"]\n61: }\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Authorization\n65: \n66: ### RBAC Model\n67: \n68: AgentCube implements Role-Based Access Control:\n69: \n70: | Role | Permissions |\n71: |------|-------------|\n72: | `admin` | Full access to all resources |\n73: | `developer` | Create, read, delete own sandboxes |\n74: | `viewer` | Read-only access |\n75: | `service` | Programmatic access for services |\n76: \n77: ### Kubernetes RBAC\n78: \n79: ```yaml\n80: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n81: kind: Role\n82: metadata:\n83:   name: agentcube-sandbox-manager\n84: rules:\n85: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n86:   resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n87:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n88: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n89:   resources: [\"pods\", \"services\"]\n90:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ## Network Isolation\n94: \n95: ### Pod Security\n96: \n97: Sandboxes run with restricted security contexts:\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: securityContext:\n101:   runAsNonRoot: true\n102:   runAsUser: 1000\n103:   allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n104:   readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n105:   capabilities:\n106:     drop:\n107:       - ALL\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Network Policies\n111: \n112: ```yaml\n113: apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\n114: kind: NetworkPolicy\n115: metadata:\n116:   name: sandbox-isolation\n117: spec:\n118:   podSelector:\n119:     matchLabels:\n120:       agentcube.volcano.sh/type: sandbox\n121:   policyTypes:\n122:   - Ingress\n123:   - Egress\n124:   ingress:\n125:   - from:\n126:     - podSelector:\n127:         matchLabels:\n128:           agentcube.volcano.sh/type: router\n129:     ports:\n130:     - protocol: TCP\n131:       port: 8080\n132:   egress:\n133:   - to:\n134:     - podSelector:\n135:         matchLabels:\n136:           agentcube.volcano.sh/type: router\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### Resource Isolation\n140: \n141: Each sandbox has dedicated resource limits:\n142: \n143: ```yaml\n144: resources:\n145:   limits:\n146:     cpu: \"2\"\n147:     memory: \"2Gi\"\n148:     ephemeral-storage: \"5Gi\"\n149:   requests:\n150:     cpu: \"500m\"\n151:     memory: \"512Mi\"\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ## Encryption\n155: \n156: ### TLS Configuration\n157: \n158: All external traffic uses TLS:\n159: \n160: ```yaml\n161: ingress:\n162:   enabled: true\n163:   tls:\n164:   - secretName: agentcube-tls\n165:     hosts:\n166:       - api.agentcube.io\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### Internal Communication\n170: \n171: Internal service-to-service communication:\n172: \n173: - Router ↔ Workload Manager: mTLS\n174: - Router ↔ Redis: TLS\n175: - Workload Manager ↔ K8s API: TLS\n176: \n177: ## Secrets Management\n178: \n179: ### Kubernetes Secrets\n180: \n181: Sensitive data stored in Kubernetes secrets:\n182: \n183: ```yaml\n184: apiVersion: v1\n185: kind: Secret\n186: metadata:\n187:   name: agentcube-secrets\n188: type: Opaque\n189: stringData:\n190:   jwt-private-key: |\n191:     -----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n192:     ...\n193:     -----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n194:   redis-password: supersecret\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ### Secret Rotation\n198: \n199: AgentCube supports automatic secret rotation:\n200: \n201: ```yaml\n202: secrets:\n203:   rotation:\n204:     enabled: true\n205:     interval: 24h\n206:     notifyOnRotation: true\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ## Auditing\n210: \n211: ### Audit Logs\n212: \n213: All operations are logged:\n214: \n215: ```json\n216: {\n217:   \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n218:   \"actor\": \"user-123\",\n219:   \"action\": \"sandbox:create\",\n220:   \"resource\": \"sandbox-456\",\n221:   \"result\": \"success\",\n222:   \"details\": {\n223:     \"image\": \"python:3.11\",\n224:     \"resources\": {\"cpu\": \"1\", \"memory\": \"512Mi\"}\n225:   }\n226: }\n227: ```\n228: \n229: ### Log Configuration\n230: \n231: ```yaml\n232: audit:\n233:   enabled: true\n234:   output: stdout\n235:   format: json\n236:   includeRequest: true\n237:   includeResponse: false\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ## Security Best Practices\n241: \n242: 1. **Enable authentication** - Never run without auth in production\n243: 2. **Use RBAC** - Grant minimum necessary permissions\n244: 3. **Enable network policies** - Isolate sandbox traffic\n245: 4. **Rotate secrets regularly** - Automate secret rotation\n246: 5. **Monitor audit logs** - Set up alerting for suspicious activity\n247: 6. **Keep updated** - Regularly update AgentCube and dependencies\n\n(End of file - total 247 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: security\ntitle: Security Architecture\nslug: /architecture/security\nsidebar_label: Security\n---\n\n## Security Overview\n\nAgentCube implements defense-in-depth security with multiple layers of protection:\n\n1. **Authentication** - Verify identity of clients\n2. **Authorization** - Control access to resources\n3. **Isolation** - Prevent cross-sandbox interference\n4. **Encryption** - Protect data in transit\n5. **Auditing** - Track all operations\n\n## Authentication\n\n### JWT Authentication","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/security.md","time":{"start":1775894960641,"end":1775894960655}}}}
