{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895085616,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b97ca3c00106uRfF3snawDZY","messageID":"msg_d7b97c15b001hSaNqydZ7QD9ff","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_10a94e3eecca4f7f856a29f7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: api-reference\ntitle: API Reference\nslug: /api-reference\nsidebar_label: API Reference\n---\n\n# API Documentation\n\nThis section provides comprehensive API documentation for all AgentCube components.\n\n## Available APIs\n\n| API | Description | Status |\n|-----|-------------|--------|\n| [Router API](/api-reference/router) | Session management and request routing | Stable |\n| [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager) | Sandbox lifecycle management | Stable |\n| [Store API](/api-reference/store) | Session state storage interface | Stable |\n| [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager) | Sandbox operations interface | Beta |\n| [PicoD API](/api-reference/picod) | In-sandbox command execution | Beta |\n\n## API Conventions\n\n### Base URLs\n\n| Environment | URL |\n|-------------|-----|\n| Development | `http://localhost:8080` |\n| Staging | `https://staging-api.agentcube.io` |\n| Production | `https://api.agentcube.io` |\n\n### Authentication\n\nAll API requests (except health endpoints) require authentication:\n\n```http\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt_token>\n```\n\n### Response Format\n\nAll responses use JSON format:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": { ... },\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n\nError responses:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": null,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\",\n    \"message\": \"Session 'sess_123' not found\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"sessionId\": \"sess_123\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP Status Codes\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| 200 | Success |\n| 201 | Created |\n| 204 | No Content |\n| 400 | Bad Request |\n| 401 | Unauthorized |\n| 403 | Forbidden |\n| 404 | Not Found |\n| 409 | Conflict |\n| 429 | Too Many Requests |\n| 500 | Internal Server Error |\n| 503 | Service Unavailable |\n\n### Versioning\n\nAPI version is included in the path:\n\n```\n/api/v1/sessions\n/api/v1/workloads\n```\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\nRate limits are enforced per client:\n\n```http\nX-RateLimit-Limit: 100\nX-RateLimit-Remaining: 95\nX-RateLimit-Reset: 1700000000\n```\n\n## Client Libraries\n\n| Language | Repository | Status |\n|----------|------------|--------|\n| Python | `sdk-python/` | Stable |\n| Go | `client-go/` | Stable |\n| CLI | `cmd/cli/` | Stable |\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Architecture Overview](/architecture/overview)\n- [Quick Start](/getting-started/quickstart)\n- [Authentication Guide](/advanced/authentication)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/README.md","time":{"start":1775895085602,"end":1775895085615}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895085620,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9800250010kr63bm61PmOxM","messageID":"msg_d7b97c15b001hSaNqydZ7QD9ff","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_55ada58ad7234ab49e958847","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: router-api\ntitle: Router API\nslug: /api-reference/router\nsidebar_label: Router API\n---\n\n# Router API\n\nThe Router API provides session management and request routing capabilities.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://router:8080/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll endpoints require JWT authentication:\n\n```http\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\n## Endpoints\n\n### Sessions\n\n#### Create Session\n\nCreates a new session and provisions a sandbox.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /sessions\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n  \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n    \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n  },\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"user\": \"alice\",\n    \"project\": \"demo\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc-456\",\n  \"status\": \"provisioning\",\n  \"endpoints\": [],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-11T16:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `201 Created` - Session created successfully\n- `400 Bad Request` - Invalid input\n- `409 Conflict` - Session already exists\n- `429 Too Many Requests` - Session limit reached\n\n#### Get Session\n\nRetrieves session information.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /sessions/{sessionId}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc-456\",\n  \"status\": \"running\",\n  \"endpoints\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"http\",\n      \"url\": \"http://sandbox-abc-456.default.svc:8080\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-11T16:30:00Z\",\n  \"lastActivity\": \"2026-04-11T15:35:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `200 OK` - Success\n- `404 Not Found` - Session not found\n\n#### Delete Session\n\nTerminates a session and cleans up resources.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nDELETE /sessions/{sessionId}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```http\nHTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `204 No Content` - Session deleted successfully\n- `404 Not Found` - Session not found\n\n### Proxy\n\n#### Proxy Request\n\nForwards requests to the sandbox instance.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /proxy/{sandboxId}/*\n```\n\n**Headers:**\n\n```http\nX-Session-ID: session-123\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n\n1. Extract session ID from header or path\n2. Validate session exists and is active\n3. Lookup sandbox endpoint from session store\n4. Forward request to sandbox\n5. Return sandbox response\n\n### Health\n\n#### Health Check\n\nLiveness probe endpoint.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /healthz\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Readiness Check\n\nReadiness probe endpoint.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /ready\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ready\",\n  \"checks\": {\n    \"redis\": \"ok\",\n    \"workloadManager\": \"ok\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Client Examples\n\n### Python SDK\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import Client\n\nclient = Client(base_url=\"http://router:8080\", token=\"your-token\")\n\n# Create session\nsession = client.create_session(\n    session_id=\"session-123\",\n    runtime=\"python-3.11\",\n    resources={\n        \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n        \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n    },\n    metadata={\n        \"user\": \"alice\",\n        \"project\": \"demo\"\n    }\n)\n\nprint(f\"Session ID: {session.id}\")\nprint(f\"Sandbox ID: {session.sandbox_id}\")\nprint(f\"Status: {session.status}\")\n\n# Get session info\nsession = client.get_session(\"session-123\")\nprint(f\"Endpoints: {session.endpoints}\")\n\n# Delete session\nclient.delete_session(\"session-123\")\n```\n\n### Go Client\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/api/v1\"\n)\n\nclient := clientgo.NewClient(\"http://router:8080\", \"your-token\")\n\n// Create session\nreq := &apiv1.CreateSessionRequest{\n    SessionID: \"session-123\",\n    Runtime:   \"python-3.11\",\n    Resources: &apiv1.ResourceRequirements{\n        CPU:    \"100m\",\n        Memory: \"256Mi\",\n    },\n}\n\nresp, err := client.CreateSession(context.Background(), req)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Session ID: %s\\n\", resp.SessionID)\nfmt.Printf(\"Sandbox ID: %s\\n\", resp.SandboxID)\n\n// Get session\nsession, err := client.GetSession(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\n\n// Delete session\nerr = client.DeleteSession(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\n```\n\n### cURL Examples\n\n```bash\n# Create session\ncurl -X POST http://router:8080/api/v1/sessions \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n    \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\"\n  }'\n\n# Get session\ncurl http://router:8080/api/v1/sessions/session-123 \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n\n# Delete session\ncurl -X DELETE http://router:8080/api/v1/sessions/session-123 \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n```\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session does not exist |\n| `SESSION_EXISTS` | 409 | Session already exists |\n| `SESSION_LIMIT_REACHED` | 429 | Maximum sessions per client exceeded |\n| `SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox not found |\n| `SANDBOX_NOT_READY` | 503 | Sandbox is not ready |\n| `INVALID_INPUT` | 400 | Invalid request parameters |\n| `UNAUTHORIZED` | 401 | Missing or invalid authentication |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED` | 429 | Rate limit exceeded |\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager)\n- [Store API](/api-reference/store)\n- [Authentication Guide](/advanced/authentication)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/router.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/router.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/router.md","time":{"start":1775895085609,"end":1775895085617}}}}
