{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895173857,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b988f2c001mIp6N3R20sQBBa","messageID":"msg_d7b98826e001HhMlFUJmKA5ONC","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_33c4a567d3344dcfb7110a8f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: workload-manager-api\ntitle: Workload Manager API\nslug: /api-reference/workload-manager\nsidebar_label: Workload Manager API\n---\n\n# Workload Manager API\n\nThe Workload Manager API provides sandbox lifecycle management and resource orchestration.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://workload-manager:8081/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nService-to-service communication requires authentication:\n\n```http\nAuthorization: Bearer <service_token>\n```\n\n## Endpoints\n\n### Sandboxes\n\n#### Create Sandbox\n\nCreates a new sandbox instance.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /sandboxes\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"requests\": {\n      \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n      \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n    },\n    \"limits\": {\n      \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n      \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n  \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n  \"podName\": \"\",\n  \"endpoints\": [],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `201 Created` - Sandbox created successfully\n- `400 Bad Request` - Invalid input\n- `409 Conflict` - Sandbox already exists\n\n#### Get Sandbox\n\nRetrieves sandbox information.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /sandboxes/{sandboxId}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n  \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"phase\": \"Running\",\n  \"podName\": \"sandbox-abc-pod-xyz\",\n  \"podIP\": \"10.244.0.5\",\n  \"endpoints\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"http\",\n      \"port\": 8080,\n      \"url\": \"http://10.244.0.5:8080\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n  \"lastActivity\": \"2026-04-11T15:35:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `200 OK` - Success\n- `404 Not Found` - Sandbox not found\n\n#### List Sandboxes\n\nLists sandboxes with optional filtering.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /sandboxes?namespace=default&phase=Running\n```\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `namespace` | string | Filter by namespace |\n| `phase` | string | Filter by phase (Pending, Running, Failed) |\n| `sessionId` | string | Filter by session ID |\n| `limit` | integer | Maximum results (default: 100) |\n| `continue` | string | Pagination token |\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sandboxes\": [\n    {\n      \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n      \"name\": \"sandbox-abc\",\n      \"namespace\": \"default\",\n      \"phase\": \"Running\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"continue\": \"eyJpZCI6InNhbmRib3gtYWJjIn0=\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Delete Sandbox\n\nDeletes a sandbox and cleans up resources.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nDELETE /sandboxes/{sandboxId}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```http\nHTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `204 No Content` - Sandbox deleted successfully\n- `404 Not Found` - Sandbox not found\n\n### AgentRuntimes\n\n#### Create AgentRuntime\n\nCreates an AgentRuntime resource.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /agentruntimes\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"python-3.11\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"image\": \"volcanosh/agentcube-python:3.11\",\n    \"resources\": {\n      \"requests\": {\n        \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n        \"memory\": \"128Mi\"\n      },\n      \"limits\": {\n        \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n        \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"env\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"PYTHONUNBUFFERED\",\n        \"value\": \"1\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"ports\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"http\",\n        \"port\": 8080,\n        \"protocol\": \"TCP\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"python-3.11\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n  \"endpoints\": [],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n#### List AgentRuntimes\n\nLists available AgentRuntimes.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /agentruntimes?namespace=default\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agentRuntimes\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"python-3.11\",\n      \"namespace\": \"default\",\n      \"image\": \"volcanosh/agentcube-python:3.11\",\n      \"phase\": \"Running\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"nodejs-18\",\n      \"namespace\": \"default\",\n      \"image\": \"volcanosh/agentcube-nodejs:18\",\n      \"phase\": \"Running\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreters\n\n#### Create CodeInterpreter\n\nCreates a CodeInterpreter resource.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /codeinterpreters\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"ci-abc-123\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"runtime\": \"python-3.11\",\n    \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n    \"resources\": {\n      \"requests\": {\n        \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n        \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n      },\n      \"limits\": {\n        \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n        \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"timeout\": \"300s\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"ci-abc-123\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"phase\": \"Pending\",\n  \"podName\": \"\",\n  \"endpoints\": [],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### Health\n\n#### Health Check\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /healthz\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Readiness Check\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /ready\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ready\",\n  \"checks\": {\n    \"kubernetes\": \"ok\",\n    \"store\": \"ok\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Client Examples\n\n### Python SDK\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import WorkloadClient\n\nclient = WorkloadClient(\n    base_url=\"http://workload-manager:8081\",\n    token=\"service-token\"\n)\n\n# Create sandbox\nsandbox = client.create_sandbox(\n    name=\"sandbox-abc\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    runtime=\"python-3.11\",\n    session_id=\"session-123\",\n    resources={\n        \"requests\": {\n            \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n            \"memory\": \"256Mi\"\n        },\n        \"limits\": {\n            \"cpu\": \"500m\",\n            \"memory\": \"512Mi\"\n        }\n    }\n)\n\nprint(f\"Sandbox ID: {sandbox.id}\")\nprint(f\"Phase: {sandbox.phase}\")\n\n# Get sandbox\nsandbox = client.get_sandbox(\"sandbox-abc\")\n\n# List sandboxes\nsandboxes = client.list_sandboxes(namespace=\"default\")\n\n# Delete sandbox\nclient.delete_sandbox(\"sandbox-abc\")\n```\n\n### Go Client\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/api/v1\"\n)\n\nclient := clientgo.NewWorkloadClient(\"http://workload-manager:8081\", \"service-token\")\n\n// Create sandbox\nreq := &apiv1.CreateSandboxRequest{\n    Name:      \"sandbox-abc\",\n    Namespace: \"default\",\n    Runtime:   \"python-3.11\",\n    SessionID: \"session-123\",\n}\n\nresp, err := client.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n\n// Get sandbox\nsandbox, err := client.GetSandbox(context.Background(), \"sandbox-abc\")\n\n// List sandboxes\nlist, err := client.ListSandboxes(context.Background(), &apiv1.ListOptions{\n    Namespace: \"default\",\n    Phase:     \"Running\",\n})\n\n// Delete sandbox\nerr = client.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), \"sandbox-abc\")\n```\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox does not exist |\n| `SANDBOX_EXISTS` | 409 | Sandbox already exists |\n| `INVALID_RUNTIME` | 400 | Invalid runtime type |\n| `VALIDATION_FAILED` | 422 | Sandbox validation failed |\n| `CREATE_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Sandbox creation timeout |\n| `RESOURCE_QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | 429 | Resource quota exceeded |\n| `INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES` | 503 | Insufficient cluster resources |\n| `K8S_API_FAILURE` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Router API](/api-reference/router)\n- [Store API](/api-reference/store)\n- [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/workload-manager.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/workload-manager.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/workload-manager.md","time":{"start":1775895173839,"end":1775895173856}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895173862,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b994772001eHnCHUkNDqNb7u","messageID":"msg_d7b98826e001HhMlFUJmKA5ONC","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bcacf1cb38a5447397651747","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: store-api\ntitle: Store API\nslug: /api-reference/store\nsidebar_label: Store API\n---\n\n# Store API\n\nThe Store API provides session state storage with Redis/Valkey backends.\n\n## Package\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n```\n\n## Interface\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    // Ping checks store connectivity\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    \n    // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox by session ID\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // StoreSandbox persists new sandbox\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    \n    // UpdateSandbox updates existing sandbox\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    \n    // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    \n    // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes expired before time\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes inactive before time\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates last activity time\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    \n    // Close closes the store connection\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### SandboxInfo\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    // Kind is the type of resource\n    Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n    \n    // SandboxID is the unique identifier for the sandbox\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    \n    // SandboxNamespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n    SandboxNamespace string `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    \n    // Name is the human-readable name\n    Name string `json:\"name\"`\n    \n    // EntryPoints are the access endpoints\n    EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    \n    // SessionID is the associated session identifier\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    \n    // CreatedAt is the creation timestamp\n    CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    \n    // ExpiresAt is the expiration timestamp\n    ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    \n    // Status is the current state\n    Status string `json:\"status\"`\n    \n    // LastActivity is the last activity timestamp\n    LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### SandboxEntryPoint\n\n```go\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    // Path is the URL path\n    Path string `json:\"path\"`\n    \n    // Protocol is the protocol (http, https, ws, wss)\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    \n    // Endpoint is the full endpoint URL\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Event Types\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    Type  EventType\n    Key   string\n    Value []byte\n}\n\ntype EventType string\n\nconst (\n    EventSet    EventType = \"set\"\n    EventDelete EventType = \"delete\"\n)\n```\n\n## Factory\n\n### Create Redis Store\n\n```go\nfunc NewRedisStore(config RedisConfig) (Store, error)\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n\n```go\ntype RedisConfig struct {\n    // Addr is the Redis address\n    Addr string `json:\"addr\" yaml:\"addr\"`\n    \n    // Password is the Redis password\n    Password string `json:\"password\" yaml:\"password\"`\n    \n    // DB is the database number\n    DB int `json:\"db\" yaml:\"db\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Create Valkey Store\n\n```go\nfunc NewValkeyStore(config ValkeyConfig) (Store, error)\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n\n```go\ntype ValkeyConfig struct {\n    // Addr is the Valkey address (comma-separated for cluster)\n    Addr string `json:\"addr\" yaml:\"addr\"`\n    \n    // Password is the Valkey password\n    Password string `json:\"password\" yaml:\"password\"`\n    \n    // DisableCache disables client-side caching\n    DisableCache bool `json:\"disableCache\" yaml:\"disableCache\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Basic Operations\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\n// Create store\ns, err := store.NewRedisStore(store.RedisConfig{\n    Addr:     \"localhost:6379\",\n    Password: \"secret\",\n    DB:       0,\n})\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\ndefer s.Close()\n\n// Check connectivity\nerr = s.Ping(context.Background())\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Store sandbox\nsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n    Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n    SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n    SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n    Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n    SessionID:        \"session-123\",\n    CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n    ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n    Status:           \"running\",\n    EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n}\n\nerr = s.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Get sandbox by session ID\nretrieved, err := s.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Update sandbox\nretrieved.Status = \"idle\"\nretrieved.LastActivity = time.Now()\nerr = s.UpdateSandbox(context.Background(), retrieved)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Update last activity\nerr = s.UpdateSessionLastActivity(context.Background(), \"session-123\", time.Now())\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// List expired sandboxes\nexpired, err := s.ListExpiredSandboxes(context.Background(), time.Now(), 100)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// List inactive sandboxes\ninactive, err := s.ListInactiveSandboxes(context.Background(), time.Now().Add(-5*time.Minute), 100)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Delete sandbox\nerr = s.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-123\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Watch for Changes\n\n```go\n// Watch for key changes (implementation dependent)\nevents, err := s.Watch(context.Background(), \"session:session-123\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfor event := range events {\n    switch event.Type {\n    case store.EventSet:\n        fmt.Printf(\"Session updated: %s\\n\", event.Key)\n    case store.EventDelete:\n        fmt.Printf(\"Session deleted: %s\\n\", event.Key)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n\n// Check for specific errors\nerr := s.StoreSandbox(ctx, info)\nif err != nil {\n    if errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound) {\n        // Handle not found\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, store.ErrConnectionFailed) {\n        // Handle connection failure\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, store.ErrSerialization) {\n        // Handle serialization error\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, store.ErrTransactionFailed) {\n        // Handle transaction failure\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Redis Key Structure\n\n| Key Pattern | Type | Description |\n|-------------|------|-------------|\n| `sandbox:{session_id}` | Hash | Sandbox metadata |\n| `sandbox:expiry` | Sorted Set | Sandboxes sorted by expiration time |\n| `sandbox:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Sandboxes sorted by last activity |\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Store backend (redis/valkey) |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Redis address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | No | - | Redis password |\n| `REDIS_DB` | No | `0` | Redis database number |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes* | - | Valkey address |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | No | - | Valkey password |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Disable client-side caching |\n\n\\* Required based on `STORE_TYPE`\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Router API](/api-reference/router)\n- [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager)\n- [Architecture Overview](/architecture/overview)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/store.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/store.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/store.md","time":{"start":1775895173847,"end":1775895173859}}}}
