{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895261113,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b99f165001tQ64CQl1YHsgrg","messageID":"msg_d7b99db11001xO24Iesuoh1V05","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_7dc845a80cfe4a7bad2a2140","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sandbox-manager-api\ntitle: Sandbox Manager API\nslug: /api-reference/sandbox-manager\nsidebar_label: Sandbox Manager API\n---\n\n# Sandbox Manager API\n\nThe Sandbox Manager API provides sandbox lifecycle management and warm pool operations.\n\n## Package\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n```\n\n## Interface\n\n```go\ntype SandboxManager interface {\n    // Create creates a new sandbox\n    Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxInfo) error\n    \n    // Update updates an existing sandbox\n    Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxInfo) error\n    \n    // Delete deletes a sandbox\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n    \n    // Get gets a sandbox by name\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // List lists sandboxes by selector\n    List(ctx context.Context, selector labels.Selector) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // WarmPool manages warm pool\n    WarmPool() WarmPoolManager\n}\n```\n\n## Warm Pool Manager\n\n```go\ntype WarmPoolManager interface {\n    // Precreate pre-creates sandboxes\n    Precreate(ctx context.Context, spec *SandboxSpec, count int) error\n    \n    // Acquire acquires a sandbox from warm pool\n    Acquire(ctx context.Context) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // Refill refills warm pool\n    Refill(ctx context.Context, spec *SandboxSpec) error\n    \n    // Size returns current warm pool size\n    Size(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n}\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### SandboxInfo\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    // Name is the sandbox name\n    Name string `json:\"name\"`\n    \n    // Namespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n    \n    // UID is the unique identifier\n    UID types.UID `json:\"uid\"`\n    \n    // RuntimeType is the runtime type\n    RuntimeType string `json:\"runtimeType\"`\n    \n    // SessionID is the associated session\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Status is the current status\n    Status SandboxStatus `json:\"status\"`\n    \n    // CreatedAt is the creation time\n    CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    \n    // ExpiresAt is the expiration time\n    ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // LastActivity is the last activity time\n    LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### SandboxSpec\n\n```go\ntype SandboxSpec struct {\n    // Image is the container image\n    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n    \n    // Resources defines resource requirements\n    Resources v1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Environment variables\n    Env []v1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Ports to expose\n    Ports []v1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // TTL is the time to live\n    TTL time.Duration `json:\"ttl,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### SandboxStatus\n\n```go\ntype SandboxStatus string\n\nconst (\n    SandboxStatusPending    SandboxStatus = \"Pending\"\n    SandboxStatusCreating   SandboxStatus = \"Creating\"\n    SandboxStatusRunning    SandboxStatus = \"Running\"\n    SandboxStatusIdle       SandboxStatus = \"Idle\"\n    SandboxStatusTerminating SandboxStatus = \"Terminating\"\n    SandboxStatusTerminated SandboxStatus = \"Terminated\"\n    SandboxStatusFailed     SandboxStatus = \"Failed\"\n)\n```\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Create Sandbox\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n)\n\n// Create manager\nmgr := sandbox.NewManager(kubeClient)\n\n// Create sandbox\nsb := &sandbox.SandboxInfo{\n    Name:        \"echo-agent-1\",\n    Namespace:   \"default\",\n    RuntimeType: \"python-3.11\",\n    SessionID:   \"session-123\",\n    Status:      sandbox.SandboxStatusPending,\n    CreatedAt:   time.Now(),\n    ExpiresAt:   time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n}\n\nerr := mgr.Create(context.Background(), sb)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Acquire from Warm Pool\n\n```go\n// Acquire sandbox from warm pool\nsb, err := mgr.WarmPool().Acquire(context.Background())\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Acquired sandbox: %s\\n\", sb.Name)\n```\n\n### Precreate Warm Pool\n\n```go\n// Precreate sandboxes\nspec := &sandbox.SandboxSpec{\n    Image: \"volcanosh/echo-agent:latest\",\n    Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n        Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n            v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n            v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n        },\n        Limits: v1.ResourceList{\n            v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"500m\"),\n            v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"512Mi\"),\n        },\n    },\n}\n\nerr := mgr.WarmPool().Precreate(context.Background(), spec, 10)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Refill warm pool when low\nerr = mgr.WarmPool().Refill(context.Background(), spec)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Check warm pool size\nsize, err := mgr.WarmPool().Size(context.Background())\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Warm pool size: %d\\n\", size)\n```\n\n### List Sandboxes\n\n```go\nimport metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\n// List all sandboxes\nlist, err := mgr.List(context.Background(), labels.Everything())\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfor _, sb := range list {\n    fmt.Printf(\"Sandbox: %s/%s - %s\\n\", sb.Namespace, sb.Name, sb.Status)\n}\n\n// List sandboxes by label\nselector, err := metav1.ParseSelector(\"runtime-type=python-3.11\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nlist, err = mgr.List(context.Background(), selector)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Update Sandbox\n\n```go\n// Get sandbox\nsb, err := mgr.Get(context.Background(), \"echo-agent-1\", \"default\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\n// Update status\nsb.Status = sandbox.SandboxStatusRunning\nsb.LastActivity = time.Now()\n\nerr = mgr.Update(context.Background(), sb)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Delete Sandbox\n\n```go\nerr := mgr.Delete(context.Background(), \"echo-agent-1\", \"default\")\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox\"\n\nerr := mgr.Create(ctx, sb)\nif err != nil {\n    if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrSandboxNotFound) {\n        // Sandbox not found\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrSandboxExists) {\n        // Sandbox already exists\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrInvalidRuntime) {\n        // Invalid runtime type\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrValidationFailed) {\n        // Validation failed\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, sandbox.ErrCreateTimeout) {\n        // Creation timeout\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `SANDBOX_DEFAULT_NAMESPACE` | No | `default` | Default namespace for sandboxes |\n| `SANDBOX_WARM_POOL_SIZE` | No | `5` | Target warm pool size |\n| `SANDBOX_WARM_POOL_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable warm pool |\n| `SANDBOX_CREATION_TIMEOUT` | No | `300s` | Sandbox creation timeout |\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager)\n- [Router API](/api-reference/router)\n- [Warm Pool Design](/advanced/warm-pool)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/sandbox-manager.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/sandbox-manager.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/sandbox-manager.md","time":{"start":1775895261099,"end":1775895261112}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895261117,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9a7f9d001zAkgqk1C56ERhj","messageID":"msg_d7b99db11001xO24Iesuoh1V05","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_504756b1098f47339339f7f9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: picod-api\ntitle: PicoD API\nslug: /api-reference/picod\nsidebar_label: PicoD API\n---\n\n# PicoD API\n\nPicoD is an in-sandbox daemon for command execution and process management.\n\n## Package\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n```\n\n## Interface\n\n```go\ntype PicoD interface {\n    // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n    Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n    \n    // Start starts a command without waiting\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n    \n    // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n    RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n    \n    // Kill terminates a running process\n    Kill(ctx context.Context, pid int) error\n    \n    // Health checks daemon health\n    Health(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Command\n\n```go\ntype Command struct {\n    // Path is the command to execute\n    Path string `json:\"path\"`\n    \n    // Args are the command arguments\n    Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Env are environment variables\n    Env []string `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Dir is the working directory\n    Dir string `json:\"dir,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Stdin is the standard input\n    Stdin io.Reader `json:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n### CommandResult\n\n```go\ntype CommandResult struct {\n    // ExitCode is the process exit code\n    ExitCode int `json:\"exitCode\"`\n    \n    // Stdout is the standard output\n    Stdout []byte `json:\"stdout,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Stderr is the standard error\n    Stderr []byte `json:\"stderr,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Duration is the execution duration\n    Duration time.Duration `json:\"duration\"`\n    \n    // OOMKilled indicates if process was OOM killed\n    OOMKilled bool `json:\"oomKilled\"`\n    \n    // Timeout indicates if execution timed out\n    Timeout bool `json:\"timeout\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Process\n\n```go\ntype Process struct {\n    // PID is the process ID\n    PID int `json:\"pid\"`\n    \n    // Command is the executed command\n    Command string `json:\"command\"`\n    \n    // StartTime is when the process started\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"startTime\"`\n    \n    // Wait returns the exit status\n    Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n    \n    // Signal sends a signal to the process\n    Signal(sig syscall.Signal) error\n}\n```\n\n### OutputHandler\n\n```go\ntype OutputHandler interface {\n    // OnStdout handles stdout chunk\n    OnStdout(chunk []byte)\n    \n    // OnStderr handles stderr chunk\n    OnStderr(chunk []byte)\n    \n    // OnComplete handles completion\n    OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n}\n```\n\n### ResourceLimits\n\n```go\ntype ResourceLimits struct {\n    // Timeout is the execution timeout\n    Timeout time.Duration `json:\"timeout\"`\n    \n    // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n    MaxMemory int64 `json:\"maxMemory\"`\n    \n    // MaxFileSize is the maximum file size in bytes\n    MaxFileSize int64 `json:\"maxFileSize\"`\n    \n    // MaxNetworkBytes is the maximum network I/O in bytes\n    MaxNetworkBytes int64 `json:\"maxNetworkBytes\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Factory\n\n### Create PicoD\n\n```go\nfunc New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) PicoD\n```\n\n**Options:**\n\n```go\n// WithWorkDir sets the working directory\nfunc WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n\n// WithLimits sets resource limits\nfunc WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n\n// WithLogger sets the logger\nfunc WithLogger(logger *zap.Logger) Option\n\n// WithTimeout sets the default timeout\nfunc WithTimeout(timeout time.Duration) Option\n```\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Basic Command Execution\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n)\n\n// Create PicoD\np := picod.New(\"sandbox-123\",\n    picod.WithWorkDir(\"/workspace\"),\n    picod.WithTimeout(30*time.Second),\n)\n\n// Run command\ncmd := &picod.Command{\n    Path: \"python\",\n    Args: []string{\"-c\", \"print('hello')\"},\n    Env:  []string{\"PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1\"},\n    Dir:  \"/workspace\",\n}\n\nresult, err := p.Run(context.Background(), cmd)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Exit code: %d\\n\", result.ExitCode)\nfmt.Printf(\"Output: %s\\n\", result.Stdout)\nfmt.Printf(\"Duration: %v\\n\", result.Duration)\n```\n\n### Streaming Output\n\n```go\ntype MyHandler struct {\n    stdout bytes.Buffer\n    stderr bytes.Buffer\n}\n\nfunc (h *MyHandler) OnStdout(chunk []byte) {\n    h.stdout.Write(chunk)\n}\n\nfunc (h *MyHandler) OnStderr(chunk []byte) {\n    h.stderr.Write(chunk)\n}\n\nfunc (h *MyHandler) OnComplete(result *picod.CommandResult) {\n    fmt.Printf(\"Completed with exit code: %d\\n\", result.ExitCode)\n}\n\n// Execute with streaming\nhandler := &MyHandler{}\nresult, err := p.RunWithStreaming(context.Background(), cmd, handler)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Long-Running Process\n\n```go\n// Start process\nproc, err := p.Start(context.Background(), &picod.Command{\n    Path: \"python\",\n    Args: []string{\"server.py\"},\n})\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Started process with PID: %d\\n\", proc.PID)\n\n// Wait for completion\nresult, err := proc.Wait()\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Process completed: %d\\n\", result.ExitCode)\n\n// Or send signal\nerr = proc.Signal(syscall.SIGTERM)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Kill Process\n\n```go\n// Kill a process by PID\nerr := p.Kill(context.Background(), 12345)\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n```\n\n### Health Check\n\n```go\nerr := p.Health(context.Background())\nif err != nil {\n    log.Fatal(err)\n}\n\nfmt.Println(\"PicoD is healthy\")\n```\n\n## HTTP Endpoints\n\nPicoD daemon exposes HTTP endpoints for remote execution.\n\n### POST /execute\n\nExecute a command.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /execute\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"command\": \"python\",\n  \"args\": [\"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n  \"env\": {\"PYTHONUNBUFFERED\": \"1\"},\n  \"dir\": \"/workspace\",\n  \"timeout\": \"30s\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"exitCode\": 0,\n  \"stdout\": \"hello\\n\",\n  \"stderr\": \"\",\n  \"duration\": \"0.1s\",\n  \"oomKilled\": false,\n  \"timeout\": false\n}\n```\n\n**Status Codes:**\n\n- `200 OK` - Command executed\n- `400 Bad Request` - Invalid request\n- `408 Timeout` - Execution timeout\n- `500 Internal Error` - Execution error\n\n### POST /start\n\nStart a long-running process.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /start\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"command\": \"python\",\n  \"args\": [\"server.py\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pid\": 12345,\n  \"command\": \"python server.py\",\n  \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### POST /kill\n\nKill a process.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nPOST /kill\n```\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pid\": 12345,\n  \"signal\": 15\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```http\nHTTP/1.1 204 No Content\n```\n\n### GET /health\n\nHealth check endpoint.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /health\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n  \"uptime\": \"1h30m\"\n}\n```\n\n### GET /processes\n\nList running processes.\n\n**Endpoint:**\n\n```http\nGET /processes\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"processes\": [\n    {\n      \"pid\": 12345,\n      \"command\": \"python server.py\",\n      \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\",\n      \"memory\": 25600000\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `PICOD_PORT` | No | `8083` | HTTP server port |\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/workspace` | Default working directory |\n| `PICOD_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default execution timeout |\n| `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n| `PICOD_SANDBOX_ID` | Yes | - | Sandbox identifier |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n\nresult, err := p.Run(ctx, cmd)\nif err != nil {\n    if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrTimeout) {\n        // Execution timed out\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrOOMKilled) {\n        // Process was OOM killed\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrNotFound) {\n        // Command not found\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, picod.ErrPermission) {\n        // Permission denied\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager)\n- [Security Architecture](/architecture/security)\n- [Code Execution Guide](/advanced/code-execution)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/picod.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/picod.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/picod.md","time":{"start":1775895261106,"end":1775895261114}}}}
