{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895326672,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9b3bad001aXTwxM3PHW7xwx","messageID":"msg_d7b9b2ff4001msm0SozDksmDnT","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_0bb04e9deb5c4d169b21678e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: coding-standards\ntitle: Coding Standards\nslug: /design/coding-standards\nsidebar_label: Coding Standards\n---\n\n# Coding Standards\n\nThis document defines the coding standards for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Go Code Standards\n\n### Code Formatting\n\nAll Go code must be formatted using standard tools:\n\n```bash\n# Format code\ngofmt -w .\n\n# Or with imports optimization\ngoimports -w .\n```\n\n**Formatting Rules:**\n\n| Rule | Standard |\n|------|----------|\n| Line width | 120 characters maximum |\n| Indentation | Tabs (not spaces) |\n| Braces | K&R style (opening brace on same line) |\n| Blank lines | Separate logical blocks |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```go\npackage router\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n)\n\n// Router handles request routing\ntype Router struct {\n    config *Config\n    store  store.Store\n}\n\n// NewRouter creates a new Router instance\nfunc NewRouter(config *Config, store store.Store) *Router {\n    return &Router{\n        config: config,\n        store:  store,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Naming Conventions\n\n#### Package Names\n\n- Use lowercase, no underscores\n- Keep names short and descriptive\n- Avoid common library names\n\n```go\n// Good\npackage router\npackage workloadmanager\npackage sandbox\n\n// Bad\npackage Router\npackage workload_manager\npackage pkg\n```\n\n#### exported Identifiers\n\n- Exported: Capital first letter\n- Private: Lowercase first letter\n\n```go\n// Exported\ntype Router struct{}\nfunc NewRouter() *Router{}\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"not found\")\n\n// Private\ntype routerConfig struct{}\nfunc (r *Router) setupRoutes() {}\nconst maxRetries = 3\n```\n\n#### Constants\n\n```go\n// Use camelCase for multi-word constants\nconst (\n    DefaultTimeout = 30 * time.Second\n    MaxRetries     = 3\n    APIVersion     = \"v1\"\n)\n```\n\n#### Variables\n\n```go\n// Short names for loop variables\nfor i := 0; i < len(items); i++ {\n    // ...\n}\n\n// Descriptive names for package-level variables\nvar (\n    defaultRouterConfig = &Config{}\n    sessionStore        store.Store\n)\n```\n\n#### Interfaces\n\n- Name interfaces with `-er` suffix for single-method interfaces\n- Use descriptive names for multi-method interfaces\n\n```go\n// Good\ntype Reader interface {\n    Read(p []byte) (n int, err error)\n}\n\ntype Store interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n\n#### Error Creation\n\n```go\n// Use errors.New for simple errors\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"router: not found\")\n\n// Use fmt.Errorf for formatted errors\nerr := fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", baseErr)\n\n// Use errors.Wrap for context\nerr := errors.Wrap(baseErr, \"router: session lookup failed\")\n```\n\n#### Error Messages\n\n- Start with lowercase\n- Do not end with punctuation\n- Include context\n\n```go\n// Good\nerrors.New(\"router: session not found\")\nfmt.Errorf(\"create sandbox: timeout after %v\", timeout)\n\n// Bad\nerrors.New(\"Router: Session Not Found.\")\nfmt.Errorf(\"Timeout!\")\n```\n\n#### Error Checking\n\n```go\n// Always check errors\nresult, err := operation()\nif err != nil {\n    return nil, err\n}\n\n// Check for specific errors\nif errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound) {\n    // Handle not found\n}\n\n// Unwrap errors\nif unwrapped := errors.Unwrap(err); unwrapped != nil {\n    // Handle wrapped error\n}\n```\n\n#### Never Ignore Errors\n\n```go\n// Good\nerr := doSomething()\nif err != nil {\n    log.Printf(\"Warning: %v\", err)\n}\n\n// Bad\n_ = doSomething() // Never do this\n```\n\n### Testing Standards\n\n#### Test Files\n\n- Name: `*_test.go`\n- Location: Same package as code being tested\n\n#### Test Functions\n\n```go\n// Use TestXxx pattern\nfunc TestRouter_CreateSession_Success(t *testing.T) {\n    // ...\n}\n\n// Use subtests for related cases\nfunc TestRouter_CreateSession(t *testing.T) {\n    t.Run(\"Success\", func(t *testing.T) {\n        // ...\n    })\n    \n    t.Run(\"InvalidInput\", func(t *testing.T) {\n        // ...\n    })\n}\n```\n\n#### Table-Driven Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestValidateInput(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        input   string\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\"valid\", \"test\", false},\n        {\"empty\", \"\", true},\n        {\"invalid\", \"test!\", true},\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            err := validateInput(tt.input)\n            if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n                t.Errorf(\"validateInput() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### Test Helpers\n\n```go\n// Use test helpers for common setup\nfunc newTestRouter(t *testing.T) *Router {\n    t.Helper()\n    \n    config := &Config{Port: 8080}\n    store := newTestStore(t)\n    return NewRouter(config, store)\n}\n```\n\n### Documentation\n\n#### Comments\n\n```go\n// Exported functions need documentation\n// NewRouter creates a new Router instance\nfunc NewRouter(config *Config, store store.Store) *Router {\n    // ...\n}\n\n// Unexported functions may have comments\n// setupRoutes initializes HTTP routes\nfunc (r *Router) setupRoutes() {\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n#### Examples\n\n```go\n// Example function for documentation\nfunc ExampleNewRouter() {\n    config := &Config{Port: 8080}\n    store := store.NewRedisStore(config.Redis)\n    router := NewRouter(config, store)\n    fmt.Println(router.config.Port)\n    // Output: 8080\n}\n```\n\n## Python Code Standards\n\n### Formatting\n\nUse Black for Python code formatting:\n\n```bash\nblack sdk-python/\n```\n\n**Rules:**\n\n| Rule | Standard |\n|------|----------|\n| Line width | 88 characters (Black default) |\n| Indentation | 4 spaces |\n| Quotes | Double quotes |\n\n### Naming\n\n```python\n# Classes: PascalCase\nclass AgentRuntime:\n    pass\n\n# Functions/variables: snake_case\ndef create_session():\n    pass\n\n# Constants: UPPER_CASE\nDEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 30\n\n# Private: _prefix\n_internal_var = None\n```\n\n## Code Review Checklist\n\n- [ ] Code formatted with gofmt/goimports\n- [ ] Naming follows conventions\n- [ ] Errors handled properly\n- [ ] Tests included for new functionality\n- [ ] Documentation comments for exported items\n- [ ] No hardcoded values (use constants)\n- [ ] No ignored errors\n- [ ] Log messages are clear and actionable\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Naming Conventions](/design/naming-conventions)\n- [Error Handling](/design/error-handling)\n- [Testing Guide](/advanced/testing)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md","time":{"start":1775895326659,"end":1775895326670}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895326676,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9bb8cd001CJe4p52dLHOQe2","messageID":"msg_d7b9b2ff4001msm0SozDksmDnT","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_79dd616f1e0541b9a3ac0c41","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: naming-conventions\ntitle: Naming Conventions\nslug: /design/naming-conventions\nsidebar_label: Naming Conventions\n---\n\n# Naming Conventions\n\nThis document defines naming conventions for the AgentCube project.\n\n## CRD Naming\n\n### Resource Names\n\nUse plural, lowercase, kebab-case for CRD names:\n\n```yaml\n# Good\nagentruntimes\ncodeinterpreters\nsandboxes\nsessions\n\n# Bad\nAgentRuntimes\nagent_runtime\nsandboxList\n```\n\n### Short Names\n\nDefine short names for common resources:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\nkind: CustomResourceDefinition\nmetadata:\n  name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\nspec:\n  names:\n    kind: AgentRuntime\n    plural: agentruntimes\n    singular: agentruntime\n    shortNames:\n    - ar\n```\n\n| Resource | Short Name |\n|----------|------------|\n| `agentruntimes` | `ar` |\n| `codeinterpreters` | `ci` |\n| `sandboxes` | `sb` |\n| `sessions` | `sess` |\n\n## API Group\n\n### Format\n\n```\n<resource>.agentcube.volcano.sh\n```\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```\nruntime.agentcube.volcano.sh\nscheduling.agentcube.volcano.sh\n```\n\n### Versions\n\nUse standard Kubernetes API versioning:\n\n```\nv1alpha1  # Alpha (breaking changes expected)\nv1beta1   # Beta (minor changes expected)\nv1        # Stable (no breaking changes)\n```\n\n**Example:**\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\n```\n\n## Kubernetes Resources\n\n### Deployments\n\n```yaml\n# Format: agentcube-{component}\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  name: agentcube-workload-manager\n  name: agentcube-agentd\n```\n\n### Services\n\n```yaml\n# Format: {component} or agentcube-{component}\nmetadata:\n  name: router\n  name: workload-manager\n  name: agentd\n```\n\n### ConfigMaps\n\n```yaml\n# Format: {component}-config\nmetadata:\n  name: router-config\n  name: workload-manager-config\n```\n\n### Secrets\n\n```yaml\n# Format: {component}-secrets or agentcube-secrets\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-secrets\n  name: redis-credentials\n```\n\n### Service Accounts\n\n```yaml\n# Format: agentcube-{component}\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router\n  name: agentcube-workload-manager\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n### Prefix\n\nUse `AGENTCUBE_` prefix for all environment variables:\n\n```bash\nAGENTCUBE_ROUTER_PORT=8080\nAGENTCUBE_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT=8081\nAGENTCUBE_STORE_TYPE=redis\nAGENTCUBE_REDIS_ADDR=localhost:6379\n```\n\n### Format\n\nUse UPPERCASE with underscores:\n\n```bash\n# Good\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_TIMEOUT\nAGENTCUBE_MAX_SESSIONS_PER_CLIENT\nAGENTCUBE_RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED\n\n# Bad\nagentcubeSessionTimeout\nAgentcubeSessionTimeout\nAGENTCUBE-SESSION-TIMEOUT\n```\n\n### Common Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level (debug, info, warn, error) |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT` | Prometheus metrics port |\n| `AGENTCUBE_HEALTH_PORT` | Health check port |\n\n## Labels and Annotations\n\n### Labels\n\nUse `agentcube.volcano.sh/` prefix for AgentCube labels:\n\n```yaml\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    agentcube.volcano.sh/component: router\n    agentcube.volcano.sh/part-of: agentcube\n    agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id: session-123\n```\n\n**Standard Labels:**\n\n| Label | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `agentcube.volcano.sh/component` | Component name |\n| `agentcube.volcano.sh/part-of` | Always \"agentcube\" |\n| `agentcube.volcano.sh/version` | Component version |\n| `agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | Session identifier |\n| `agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-id` | Sandbox identifier |\n\n### Annotations\n\nUse `agentcube.io/` prefix for annotations:\n\n```yaml\nmetadata:\n  annotations:\n    agentcube.io/created-by: \"workload-manager\"\n    agentcube.io/last-activity: \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n```\n\n## File Names\n\n### Go Files\n\n```\n# Lowercase with underscores\nconfig.go\nsandbox_processor.go\nsandbox_processor_test.go\n```\n\n### Python Files\n\n```\n# Lowercase with underscores\nagent_runtime.py\ncode_interpreter.py\ntest_agent_runtime.py\n```\n\n### Configuration Files\n\n```yaml\n# Kebab-case\nrouter-config.yaml\nworkload-manager-values.yaml\n```\n\n## Database Keys\n\n### Redis Keys\n\nUse colon-separated hierarchy:\n\n```\n# Format: component:type:id\nrouter:session:session-123\nrouter:ratelimit:client-456\nworkload:sandbox:sandbox-abc\nstore:expiry:timestamp\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Type | Description |\n|---------|------|-------------|\n| `session:{id}` | Hash | Session metadata |\n| `sandbox:{id}` | Hash | Sandbox metadata |\n| `sandbox:expiry` | Sorted Set | Expiration index |\n| `sandbox:activity` | Sorted Set | Activity index |\n| `ratelimit:{client}` | String | Rate counter |\n\n## Error Codes\n\n### Format\n\nUse UPPER_CASE with underscores:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    ERR_INVALID_INPUT       = \"ERR_INVALID_INPUT\"\n    ERR_SESSION_NOT_FOUND   = \"ERR_SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ERR_SANDBOX_EXISTS      = \"ERR_SANDBOX_EXISTS\"\n    ERR_TIMEOUT             = \"ERR_TIMEOUT\"\n    ERR_INTERNAL            = \"ERR_INTERNAL\"\n)\n```\n\n### Prefixes\n\n| Prefix | Category |\n|--------|----------|\n| `ERR_` | General errors |\n| `WARN_` | Warnings |\n| `EVENT_` | Events |\n\n## Go Types\n\n### Structs\n\nUse PascalCase for struct names:\n\n```go\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    Port int `json:\"port\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    ID string `json:\"id\"`\n}\n```\n\n### JSON Tags\n\nUse camelCase for JSON field names:\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SandboxID    string    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    CreatedAt    time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    EntryPoints  []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n}\n```\n\n### YAML Tags\n\nUse kebab-case for YAML field names:\n\n```go\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    Port       int    `yaml:\"port\"`\n    SessionTTL string `yaml:\"sessionTtl\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Coding Standards](/design/coding-standards)\n- [Error Handling](/design/error-handling)\n- [API Reference](/api-reference)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/naming-conventions.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/naming-conventions.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/naming-conventions.md","time":{"start":1775895326664,"end":1775895326673}}}}
