{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895372302,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9c3a67001UaSEIu7h5Jb6AP","messageID":"msg_d7b9c3006001A53RCiQrFae1cY","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_31b9c9bece6d4c8bb98f0869","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: error-handling\ntitle: Error Handling\nslug: /design/error-handling\nsidebar_label: Error Handling\n---\n\n# Error Handling\n\nThis document defines error handling patterns and conventions for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Error Types\n\n### Application Errors\n\n```go\npackage router\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n    ErrCodeSessionNotFound     = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrCodeSessionExists       = \"SESSION_EXISTS\"\n    ErrCodeSandboxNotReady     = \"SANDBOX_NOT_READY\"\n    ErrCodeRateLimitExceeded   = \"RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED\"\n    ErrCodeUnauthorized        = \"UNAUTHORIZED\"\n    ErrCodeInvalidInput        = \"INVALID_INPUT\"\n    ErrCodeInternalError       = \"INTERNAL_ERROR\"\n)\n\n// Error variables\nvar (\n    ErrSessionNotFound     = errors.New(\"router: session not found\")\n    ErrSessionExists       = errors.New(\"router: session already exists\")\n    ErrSandboxNotReady     = errors.New(\"router: sandbox not ready\")\n    ErrRateLimitExceeded   = errors.New(\"router: rate limit exceeded\")\n    ErrUnauthorized        = errors.New(\"router: unauthorized\")\n    ErrInvalidInput        = errors.New(\"router: invalid input\")\n    ErrInternalError       = errors.New(\"router: internal error\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Struct\n\nFor structured error responses:\n\n```go\ntype Error struct {\n    // Code is the error code\n    Code string `json:\"code\"`\n    \n    // Message is the human-readable message\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n    \n    // Details contains additional context\n    Details map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Cause is the underlying error\n    Cause error `json:\"-\"`\n}\n\nfunc (e *Error) Error() string {\n    if e.Cause != nil {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", e.Message, e.Cause)\n    }\n    return e.Message\n}\n\nfunc (e *Error) Unwrap() error {\n    return e.Cause\n}\n```\n\n## Error Creation\n\n### Simple Errors\n\n```go\n// Use errors.New for static errors\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n### Formatted Errors\n\n```go\n// Use fmt.Errorf for dynamic errors\nfunc (s *Store) Get(key string) ([]byte, error) {\n    if key == \"\" {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"key cannot be empty\")\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Wrapped Errors\n\n```go\n// Use errors.Wrap for context\nfunc CreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, spec *SandboxSpec) (*Sandbox, error) {\n    if err := validate(spec); err != nil {\n        return nil, errors.Wrap(err, \"validate sandbox spec\")\n    }\n    \n    sandbox, err := k8sClient.Create(ctx, spec)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, errors.Wrap(err, \"create sandbox in Kubernetes\")\n    }\n    \n    return sandbox, nil\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling Patterns\n\n### Check Errors Immediately\n\n```go\n// Good\nresult, err := operation()\nif err != nil {\n    return nil, err\n}\n\n// Bad\nresult, _ := operation() // Never ignore errors\n```\n\n### Return Errors Up\n\n```go\n// Let callers decide how to handle errors\nfunc getUser(id string) (*User, error) {\n    user, err := db.Find(id)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err // Don't log here\n    }\n    return user, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Add Context at Boundaries\n\n```go\n// Add context at API boundaries\nfunc (h *Handler) CreateSession(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    session, err := h.service.CreateSession(r.Context(), req)\n    if err != nil {\n        if errors.Is(err, service.ErrSessionExists) {\n            respondError(w, http.StatusConflict, \"session already exists\")\n        } else {\n            log.Printf(\"CreateSession failed: %v\", err)\n            respondError(w, http.StatusInternalServerError, \"internal error\")\n        }\n        return\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Classification\n\n### Retryable Errors\n\n```go\n// Errors that can be retried\nfunc IsRetryableError(err error) bool {\n    return errors.Is(err, ErrTimeout) ||\n           errors.Is(err, ErrServiceUnavailable) ||\n           errors.Is(err, ErrConnectionRefused)\n}\n\n// Usage with retry\nresult, err := retry(ctx, 3, func() (interface{}, error) {\n    return operation()\n})\n```\n\n### Non-Retryable Errors\n\n```go\n// Errors that should not be retried\nfunc IsTerminalError(err error) bool {\n    return errors.Is(err, ErrNotFound) ||\n           errors.Is(err, ErrUnauthorized) ||\n           errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidInput)\n}\n```\n\n## HTTP Error Responses\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\",\n    \"message\": \"Session 'session-123' not found\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T15:30:00Z\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Status Code Mapping\n\n| Error | HTTP Status | Error Code |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| NotFound | 404 | `{RESOURCE}_NOT_FOUND` |\n| AlreadyExists | 409 | `{RESOURCE}_ALREADY_EXISTS` |\n| Unauthorized | 401 | `UNAUTHORIZED` |\n| Forbidden | 403 | `FORBIDDEN` |\n| InvalidInput | 400 | `INVALID_INPUT` |\n| ValidationFailed | 422 | `VALIDATION_FAILED` |\n| RateLimitExceeded | 429 | `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED` |\n| InternalError | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` |\n| ServiceUnavailable | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` |\n| Timeout | 504 | `TIMEOUT` |\n\n### Handler Example\n\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRequest(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    result, err := h.service.Process(r.Context(), r.Body)\n    if err != nil {\n        h.writeError(w, err)\n        return\n    }\n    h.writeJSON(w, http.StatusOK, result)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, err error) {\n    var (\n        status int\n        code   string\n    )\n    \n    switch {\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrNotFound):\n        status = http.StatusNotFound\n        code = \"NOT_FOUND\"\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidInput):\n        status = http.StatusBadRequest\n        code = \"INVALID_INPUT\"\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrUnauthorized):\n        status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n        code = \"UNAUTHORIZED\"\n    default:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        code = \"INTERNAL_ERROR\"\n        log.Printf(\"Unexpected error: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    h.writeJSON(w, status, ErrorResponse{\n        Code:    code,\n        Message: err.Error(),\n    })\n}\n```\n\n## Logging Errors\n\n### Log with Context\n\n```go\n// Include relevant context\nlog.Printf(\"Failed to create session for client %s: %v\", clientID, err)\n```\n\n### Log Levels\n\n```go\n// Debug: Detailed information\nlog.Debugf(\"Processing request: %+v\", request)\n\n// Info: Normal operations\nlog.Infof(\"Session created: %s\", sessionID)\n\n// Warn: Recoverable errors\nlog.Warnf(\"Rate limit approaching for client %s\", clientID)\n\n// Error: Operation failures\nlog.Errorf(\"Failed to delete session %s: %v\", sessionID, err)\n```\n\n### Structured Logging\n\n```go\nlog.WithFields(log.Fields{\n    \"session_id\": sessionID,\n    \"client_id\":  clientID,\n    \"action\":     \"create\",\n}).WithError(err).Error(\"Failed to create session\")\n```\n\n## Panic Handling\n\n### Avoid Panics\n\n```go\n// Good: Return errors\nfunc parseInput(data []byte) (*Input, error) {\n    if len(data) == 0 {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"empty input\")\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n\n// Bad: Panic on error\nfunc parseInput(data []byte) *Input {\n    if len(data) == 0 {\n        panic(\"empty input\") // Don't do this\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Recover from Panics\n\n```go\n// Use defer/recover at boundaries\nfunc safeHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    defer func() {\n        if rec := recover(); rec != nil {\n            log.Errorf(\"Panic recovered: %v\", rec)\n            http.Error(w, \"internal error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n        }\n    }()\n    \n    handle(w, r)\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Errors\n\n### Test Error Cases\n\n```go\nfunc TestCreateSession_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n    store := &mockStore{err: store.ErrNotFound}\n    handler := NewHandler(store)\n    \n    _, err := handler.CreateSession(context.Background(), req)\n    \n    assert.Error(t, err)\n    assert.True(t, errors.Is(err, ErrSessionNotFound))\n}\n```\n\n### Table-Driven Error Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestValidateInput(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        input   string\n        wantErr error\n    }{\n        {\"empty\", \"\", ErrInputEmpty},\n        {\"invalid\", \"test!\", ErrInputInvalid},\n        {\"valid\", \"test\", nil},\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            err := validateInput(tt.input)\n            assert.ErrorIs(t, err, tt.wantErr)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Coding Standards](/design/coding-standards)\n- [Router API Error Codes](/api-reference/router#error-codes)\n- [Workload Manager API Error Codes](/api-reference/workload-manager#error-codes)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/error-handling.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/error-handling.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/error-handling.md","time":{"start":1775895372291,"end":1775895372299}}}}
