{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895407187,"sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9ced6a0015OkFA4cBQ11weU","messageID":"msg_d7b9ce239001bceLQCuUdZkBUQ","sessionID":"ses_2846a2e6bffespSqc0M4jSfCzg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_acd5a44ed9ac4bcb994f467a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Documentation\n\nWelcome to the AgentCube documentation repository. This directory contains comprehensive technical documentation for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Documentation Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── README.md                          # This file - documentation guide\n├── architecture/                      # Architecture design documentation\n│   ├── overview.md                    # System architecture overview\n│   ├── components.md                  # Core component designs\n│   ├── data-flow.md                   # Data flow and request processing\n│   ├── deployment.md                  # Deployment architectures\n│   └── security.md                    # Security architecture\n├── api/                               # API documentation\n│   ├── README.md                      # API documentation index\n│   ├── router.md                      # Router API reference\n│   ├── workload-manager.md            # Workload Manager API reference\n│   ├── store.md                       # Store API reference\n│   ├── sandbox-manager.md             # Sandbox Manager API reference\n│   └── picod.md                       # PicoD API reference\n├── design/                            # Design specifications\n│   ├── coding-standards.md            # Go coding standards\n│   ├── naming-conventions.md          # Naming conventions\n│   └── error-handling.md              # Error handling specification\n└── docs/                              # Docusaurus site source (AR-042)\n    ├── docs/\n    │   ├── architecture/              # Rendered architecture docs\n    │   ├── api/                       # Rendered API docs\n    │   └── design/                    # Rendered design specs\n    └── ...\n```\n\n## Reader Guide\n\n### For Developers\n\nStart here if you're developing with or contributing to AgentCube:\n\n1. **[Architecture Overview](/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md)** - Understand system design\n2. **[API Reference](/docs/docs/api/README.md)** - Learn available APIs\n3. **[Coding Standards](/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md)** - Follow project conventions\n4. **[Quick Start](/docs/docs/getting-started/quickstart.md)** - Get started quickly\n\n### For Architects\n\nFocus on high-level design and decisions:\n\n1. **[Architecture Overview](/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md)** - System vision and layers\n2. **[Component Design](/docs/docs/architecture/components.md)** - Core component responsibilities\n3. **[Data Flow](/docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md)** - Request processing flows\n4. **[Security Architecture](/docs/docs/architecture/security.md)** - Security model\n5. **[Deployment Architecture](/docs/docs/architecture/deployment.md)** - Deployment patterns\n\n### For Operators\n\nFocus on deployment and operations:\n\n1. **[Deployment Architecture](/docs/docs/architecture/deployment.md)** - Deployment modes\n2. **[Kubernetes Deployment](/docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md)** - K8s installation\n3. **[Helm Deployment](/docs/docs/deployment/helm.md)** - Helm chart usage\n4. **[Monitoring Guide](/docs/docs/advanced/monitoring.md)** - Observability setup\n\n## Documentation Categories\n\n### Architecture Documentation (`architecture/`)\n\nTechnical design documents describing system architecture:\n\n- **overview.md** - System vision, layers, and components\n- **components.md** - Detailed component designs\n- **data-flow.md** - Request flows and state machines\n- **deployment.md** - Deployment architectures (dev, staging, production)\n- **security.md** - Security model and measures\n\n### API Documentation (`api/`)\n\nComplete API reference for all components:\n\n- **router.md** - Session management and routing API\n- **workload-manager.md** - Sandbox lifecycle API\n- **store.md** - Storage interface and operations\n- **sandbox-manager.md** - Sandbox operations and warm pool\n- **picod.md** - In-sandbox command execution API\n\n### Design Specifications (`design/`)\n\nCoding standards and design conventions:\n\n- **coding-standards.md** - Go and Python coding standards\n- **naming-conventions.md** - Naming rules for all identifiers\n- **error-handling.md** - Error handling patterns and conventions\n\n## Relationship with Docusaurus (AR-042)\n\nThis documentation serves as the **source of truth** for the AgentCube project. The content is synchronized with the Docusaurus documentation site (AR-042):\n\n| Aspect | This Repository (AR-043) | Docusaurus Site (AR-042) |\n|--------|-------------------------|-------------------------|\n| **Purpose** | Source documentation | Rendered documentation site |\n| **Format** | Markdown files | React/Markdown with navigation |\n| **Location** | `docs/docs/` | Built and deployed site |\n| **Audience** | Developers (direct access) | All users (web interface) |\n| **Updates** | Edit markdown files | Automatic on build |\n\n### Workflow\n\n1. Write/update documentation in `docs/docs/`\n2. Commit changes to repository\n3. CI/CD builds Docusaurus site\n4. Site deployed with updated content\n\n## Documentation Standards\n\n### File Format\n\n- All documentation uses Markdown (`.md`)\n- Files use UTF-8 encoding\n- Line endings are Unix-style (LF)\n\n### Front Matter\n\nAll markdown files include Docusaurus front matter:\n\n```yaml\n---\nid: overview\ntitle: Architecture Overview\nslug: /architecture/overview\nsidebar_label: Overview\n---\n```\n\n### Diagrams\n\nUse Mermaid for diagrams when possible:\n\n````markdown\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[Client] --> B[Router]\n    B --> C[Redis]\n    B --> D[Sandbox]\n```\n````\n\nOr ASCII art for simple diagrams:\n\n```\nClient → Router → Redis → Sandbox\n```\n\n### Code Examples\n\nAlways specify the language for code blocks:\n\n````markdown\n```go\npackage main\n\nfunc main() {\n    fmt.Println(\"Hello, World!\")\n}\n```\n````\n\n```python\nprint(\"Hello, World!\")\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\n### Updating Documentation\n\n1. Edit the appropriate markdown file\n2. Follow existing structure and style\n3. Update front matter if needed\n4. Run `npm run build` in `docs/` to verify\n5. Submit pull request\n\n### Adding New Sections\n\n1. Create new markdown file in appropriate directory\n2. Add front matter with unique `id` and `slug`\n3. Update `sidebars.ts` to add to navigation\n4. Cross-reference from existing documents\n\n### Review Checklist\n\n- [ ] Spelling and grammar correct\n- [ ] Code examples are accurate and tested\n- [ ] Diagrams render correctly\n- [ ] Links work (internal and external)\n- [ ] Follows naming conventions\n- [ ] Consistent with existing content\n- [ ] Front matter is correct\n\n## Tools\n\n### Local Development\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\ncd docs\nnpm install\n\n# Start development server\nnpm run start\n\n# Build for production\nnpm run build\n\n# Run tests\nnpm run test\n```\n\n### Validation\n\n```bash\n# Check markdown links\nnpm run check-links\n\n# Verify front matter\nnpm run check-frontmatter\n```\n\n## Versioning\n\nDocumentation follows AgentCube versioning:\n\n- **Main branch** - Latest development version\n- **Release branches** - Version-specific documentation (e.g., `release-0.1`)\n- **Tags** - Snapshots at release points\n\n## Related Documents\n\n- [Project Overview](../../project.md)\n- [Design Specification](../../design.md)\n- [Contributing Guide](../../CONTRIBUTING.md)\n- [AR-042 Proposal](../../changes/AR-042/proposal.md)\n\n## Support\n\nFor documentation issues or questions:\n\n- **GitHub Issues** - Report documentation bugs\n- **Discussions** - Ask questions\n- **Slack** - Real-time chat support\n\n## License\n\nDocumentation is licensed under the same license as the AgentCube project.\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/README.md","time":{"start":1775895407175,"end":1775895407184}}}}
